\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 The first thing I want to know is where you were born and what year you were born in
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I was born in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Woodstock{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, in - is 1880, it would be wouldn't it, yes, 'cos I'm ninety-three now, well that was it, born in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Woodstock{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What was the name of the house you were born in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 It was - oh - no - I don't think in that time the ho
uses was named. Oh wait a minute. Yes. I was born in Burns Cottage, that's a cottage - next to the doctor's surgery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Could you tell me what year you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No I can't. Thirty-two. No I can't. I've been married - thirty-two - forty-two, fi
fty-two, sixty-two, seventy-two - eighty-two, I've been married sixty years, can you get it from that. As near as I can say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Do you remember how many years you lived in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, only a very short period.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 And then you moved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Where did you move to then, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 We moved then - into that house - next to Mr Whitlock's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 That would be on {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Oxford Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 This here, next to Mr. Whitlock. And that house - my parents was the first to 
go into when it was complete. Then from there - we went - to the one up the street - same street where Mr Jerram's lived. Did you know that? Well you know I think now there used to be a grocers shop on each side, but the one I think now is still a grocers
 shop, but this side I think they've made into a sort of restaurant, I don't know now anything. Well then we moved into that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What year would that be, have you any idea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How old would you have been, eight or nine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. About seven 
I think. And then from there - you see, we came here, 'cos father was - in business and he wanted a stable, and - we came here and I suppose I've been in here about - seventy - oh, must have been here eighty years in this house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 So you were about ten when you came here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Mm? Yes, about - yes. Is that near enough? Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You stayed in here until you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes, and I shall stay here 'til I pass out. Unless I have to be sold up and go into a home. Which heaven forbid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Could you tell me how many brothers and sisters you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I had one brother. He died at nineteen. Yes. That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Was he older than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, he was ten years younger and he was my idol.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Can you tell me how old your father was when you were born, any idea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Forty-two - I should think about four and twenty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Do you know where he came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Born in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Woodstock{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. In Old 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Woodstock{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. We're getting on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 And he was a chimney sweep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 In his early days and then of course he went into t
he coal business. And my husband you see - we all lived together you see, in fact my - my husband was in the business in the coal business with father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When did he stop being a chimney sweep and go into the coal business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When what? Well 'til he was seventy, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 He was a sweep as well all the time he worked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Oh yes, he used to do all the Blenheim chimneys. I'm proud of it you know. Then father - was the - he belonged to the first fire brigade that was started. I have two of his l
ong service medals. My husband also was in it but of course later years. But my brother was ambulance.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 He was in the fire brigade and he was a chimney sweep and a coalman, did he do any other}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9926461\charrsid5728063  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 work, not that he had much time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Can you remember about your mother, can you remember how old your mother would have been when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Mother would have been about two and twenty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Essex{\*\xmlclose}. Rayleigh. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you know if she had any jobs before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 She had plenty after. No, mother was a general servant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 In {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Woodstock{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No - I don't think mother was in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Woodstock{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} 'til she was married. No, I don't think she was. A funny thing someone was talking to me about something the other day and they said, well - it happened in Kensington, oh I said, and that's where my father and mother were married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Your father was in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} then?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Father was working in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 then as a sweep you see, not in business for his own. He was - journeyman sweep you see in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Was he apprenticed in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} too?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 He was apprenticed then. Well then - father's father - he was a chimney sweep and we were talking the other day about the - 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Oxford{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} chimney sweep, what's his name? And I said, wel
l then, his business - went as far back as ours 'cos - this chimney sweep you see business was grandpa Morgan's, well that's over a hundred years ago. It's interesting you know when - want to go back over it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You said your mother worked a lot after she was married, can you remember the jobs that she did after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Well - well mother stayed at home and looked after her home then. They didn't go out to work. I said to someone the other day, talking about the \{ILLEGIBLE\} work, I said, ye
s, I know the time if a woman went out to work her husband looked on it as an insult to himself. Don't you think so? Looked as if he couldn't afford to keep her. They laughed at me, well, I said, it's true enough. I says, they wouldn't no more thought of 
going out to work and leaving their home then they would have flying. I says, and who's paying the price now? The children. I reckon.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Can you remember - after you moved from Burns cottage to the house up the road, how many rooms were in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes. In Burns cottage? Oh I don't remember, goodness I wasn't very old when we came out of it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 But when you moved to the other one by the grocers shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Next to the - Mr Jerram's? There was two rooms downstairs, this will all be expos
ed will it? Oh. That one there where Mr Jerrams lived there was a front room and a kitchen and three bedrooms and an attic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How many rooms are there here? Quite a lot aren't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well there's three bedrooms on this floor and four rooms down, and two attics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When you were a child did anybody live with you in the house apart from your parents and your brother and you,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I think our home for years was the refuge of many. Relatives and friends, and it's only this latter years I've been abl
e to enjoy my home on my own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 The reguge of many, relatives who were looking for work or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Mm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Why did the relatives come and stay with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well they were aged and invalids and - and that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Right from when you were a child you remember that do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Your grandparents lived with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Grandma would, mother's mother died here, she was - we was laughing the other day, I said well - grandma was bedridden six years and it seems as if I've got the sam
e fate. 'Course - father, he was a bronchial asthma subject, and - he had some bad weeks, but - I went into his room one morning and he said - I should like another cup of tea. Well, I says, I'll go down and make a fresh cup. And I stood by the bedside ho
l
ding the hot - cup - saucer, he got the cup and - and put the cup back and gave me a smile and that was the finish. Mm. Nice death, mm. He was eighty-six. Mother was eighty-two. I don't know how I shall be, some of 'em think I shall see a century. Well I 
says, I shall have worn all the bed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9926461\charrsid5728063 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 linen out by that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your mother pay anybody to help in the house with the cleaning or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 We had a woman to do the washing, that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 She came in the house to do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, she - oh she did it here, see you've got the wash house and the well and all with close - here, you going to put all that down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How did you get on with the lady came, did you like her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 We had two different wash ladies. One was here fifteen years, the other was sixteen and the last one was here with twenty-seven years.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Were they young when they came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh fairly young, married women - two were married women, one had never married. I said she chose the better path perhaps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Can you remember what she called your mother, did she call her ma'am or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh no, Mrs. Mrs Morgan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did she call you anything special when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh I don't think - I was generally Ethel, that was my name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your mother or father make or mend the family clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, that fell to my lot. I did all the making. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How old were you when you started that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh I was in a workroom you see. And - oh I did all the needlework.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 But when you were six or seven years old did your mother do it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, mother didn't like needlework.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 So she'd have bought the clothes from a shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Mother was the housewife. Of course I did a lot of housework but - oh I had my sewing machine. I was never idle. I tell 'em now so long 
as holiday I've ever had, this is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did she buy your clothes when you were children, did she buy them from the shops?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 In {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Woodstock{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 They were bought new were they, never second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9926461\charrsid5728063  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh no. No, never even went to a jumble sale.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Do you know if they were bought at any special time of the year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 If they what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When did they buy the clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh when we wanted clothes. Oh yes. Oh mother was a good manager and always quiet, she never went ou
t nor much - much you know. Someone said to me one day, coming - she said, doesn't Mr Morgan - that was my father, and your husband go out at night? No, I says, they don't, they're too tired, they want to sit by the fire with the paper. I said, and we did
 know where they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your father mend the shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
No. Oh he only stuck to his own grade. But my husband - he was apprenticed in Banbury. I don't know what you - tin work and all that sort of thing. And then - his - the man he worked for went
 bankrupt, are you taking this all down? And he came here, until his father could find him - his own work, but he didn't go away. He wanted to be with the horses, he didn't go away, and I suppose I fell into it you see and - we married. And we was all in 
the business. Oh they were happy days. But my chief interest was me garden. I loved garden. I should like to have been a florist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your father help your mother around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. I heard of a man the other day said he didn't do anything in 
the house, that was a woman's job. No, he was very good but - well they hadn't time you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 He worked long hours did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes, it was generally {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 16}}}four o'clock{\*\xmlclose} in the morning when people got spring cleaning fever and - that sort of thing. Well folks don't know about work today. I said those days you know I said it was - 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}}eight o'clock{\*\xmlclose} in the morning 'til {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 19}}}seven o'clock{\*\xmlclose} at night and no Thursday afternoon. But - they don't believe it now if you tell 'em that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did he do any decorating in the house or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
No, nothing of that. Nothing of that, just their own trade. Chimney sweeping and the coal, but of course my husband was good at his trade, he could do anything in metal where tinkering and all that sort of thing. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What about with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 We had no children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Your father, with you, when you were children, did he read you stories at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Not help get you ready for bed or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. No, that was mother's - you see, all
 through - up 'til the time I was ten years olf old, I was never well long together. Now I've lived to this age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 But when you weren't well your mother was always the one that looked after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Mother looked after everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 After you were ten when you got a bit better did your father ever take you out for the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh used to go out in the pony and trap sometimes in the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Would that be just your father and you and your brother, or your mother as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, father and I
 generally went alone and Henry stayed with mother and my husband was generally tinkering, he got a shop at the bottom of the garden you see. And - mother and I of course were both very fond of reading, well I got all me books there now you see on the - s
o it was never dull.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Where would you go with your father in the pony and trap, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Oh anywhere round the villages. Yes. They were nice nights, I used to love that pony and trap. But still, as they say, they didn't want much to do in the evening, they worked too hard in the day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
When you were at home, between when you were ten and when you went to the workroom, did you have any jobs you had to do in the house? To help your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh I did a certain amount, I alw
ays looked after my own bedroom, and I always had the shopping to do, that's one thing mother would not do. Soon as I was old enough I had to do the shopping. And I used to say sometimes, well mother - I don't want to go. Well it's like this my child, if 
you don't go they won't have anything for I'm not going, and she never would. Funny wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you go on doing these sort of things after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes, and then you see when we were married we still stayed in the house, we had our own
 rooms, my husband and I, but - but - oh I kept on the routine you know. After we married I didn't go out in the workroom you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Can you remember did you help your brother with things he found difficult, like getting dressed and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, he was in the drapery you know. At - London House, Mr Banbury's - Henry was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 But when you were very small, when he was a baby, did you help look after him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Mm. Yes. I did, father always said mother - him and I brought Henry up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What sort of things did you do? Did you help him get dressed and undressed and this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Who Henry? Oh. No, I only helped look after him, take him out and play with him. And - he's a lovely boy. We had a - he had his last illness, we had - had 
Aclland Home nurse in the house - some weeks with him and two or three doctors but he slipped through. Yes, and I was always the ailing one and I stuck it. Strange isn't it, life is strange you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When you were still at school when you were still living at home were you expected to go to bed at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did I what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you have to go to bed at a certain time when you were young?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes. Yes. That was the one thing doctor and I were laughing about this morning, talking about som
e child up 'til ten o'clock at night, well, he said, Mrs Morgan, but they all do that now. I said, well I should think they do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What time did you have to go to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I used to go between eight and nine. Is that all going in there? They'll sort it out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What about - who put you to bed, did your mother put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Mother. Mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did she tell you a story or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, I was too sleepy and she didn't want to keep me awake just - sleep was the main thing for me. Yes, a nice time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How old were you when you started putting yourself to bed, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Well you see when Henry came I was ten years of age and I had to do a lot for myself then that I'd never done you see. But he was never a trial to me. I
 was laughing the other day, he always called me Liz. You see my name was Elizabeth. And - he couldn't say Ethel, and so my mother says, well you should call her Liz, and he always did. And that was the only time he - I ever knew if he was annoyed with me
, and he called me Ethel then, I thought, hello, something's gone wrong, but I said the other day I couldn't answer to that name now after read - reading so much about Liz Burton. Well do you blame me?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you share the bedroom in any of the houses you lived in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. I had my own room. I had my own room from the time boy came.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I slept in mother's room. Had my own - single bed of course. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Can you remember when you first came here where everybody slept, you had your own room did you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
That was father and mother's room next there, and this was my room. And my husband, before we were married - he had that room. And my brother as he got older he had a single bed in there as well you see. Oh we were very well accommodated.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you have a bathroom or anything?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, we hadn't that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Where did you bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 We had the big bath in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 In front of the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Mm, yes, by the fire. I couldn't be without a fire, that's the - up here you
 see, downstairs right from the end I had my kitchen fire, I said the other day, well it would be hopeless now because the coal's so dear isn't it, but we've never }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9926461\charrsid5728063 
- I was never without a fire. Al}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 l day, winter and summer. 'Til I had the gas fire here you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How often did you have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh - twice a week. But you see - yes, about twice a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you have your clean clothes on then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes. Oh yes. Oh yes. Yes, they were nice days. Plenty of work, I loved me garden and I loved me a
nimals. I've missed that very much. Still you can't have everything. I - miss me animals. Still there's other things to take their place. If you look at it in that light. There's one thing I don't hear ambulance when it goes by, I can't hear that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Can you remember where the family had their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Where they had it? Oh we had them in the kitchen. In the working days. And then of course when the working days we had it in the big middle room down there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 That was on a Sunday in the big room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
We had all our meals there on a Sunday, and usually a supper at nights. I hope you'll sort all that out you know. You know I had a record on my birthday this years, I don't know who did it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What was it a record of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 All my - it wish me many h
appy returns of the day, and - they - they played - a Harry Secombe's Bless This House, but who did it I don't know. Wasn't it nice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Where did your mother cook in the kitchen, did she have a range or a gas stove?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 We had a kitchen range, it's the
re now the big kitchen range, and then I - I had - only recently had a new gas stove. I'd had one for a long time, but you see I'm not a lover of electricity. I don't like electricity. But - of course I got it for lights and - there's two rooms downstairs
 but - it's only to keep 'em aired, I couldn't sit with an electric fire, knocks all the energy out of me.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Can you tell me what time you had breakfast in the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 In breakfast? Well you see there was no set time, sometimes they had to be out at 
between four and five in the morning, they just had their cup of tea, got the - well father always got it, and - I - that's one thing I should - shouldn't settle to meals at any time, you know, some - go in one time, well mother says I shouldn't put up wi
th that. I said, when a woman has had half the morning - shopping and cooking - it is hard if a man can't study them to extent of being - well I says I wouldn't keep it on, so there's that - and they knew I wouldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 So you didn't all have breakfast together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, father and - my husband had theirs and then - well - father used to bring mother's and mine upstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 So father would have his breakfast in the kitchen
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes, and George. Mother and I had it upstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Can you remember what you had to eat and drink at breakfast times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Oh it was only bread and butter and cheese. Well I don't know that father had any food, he just wanted his cup of tea, that's all we had. We never wet in for cooked breakfasts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your father come back to have something later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh no, he - they went straight out to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you have different breakfasts on special days, on Sunday or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. Always kept to the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 But on Sunday you all had breakfast together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes. And our meals, in the middle room, the big room downstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You had breakfast in the big room downstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes. Yes. And then - that little - room as you come in the front door this side, that was father's office you see, and when he gave 
up - work, he was in that room, that was my first job of the morning, get the fire and ready for him you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 That would be a bit later on though, much later on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Mm? Yes, he kept on working 'til he was seventy and then - he only knocked off - i
n autumn and winter, he started again in the spring, as long as the weather was good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What did you have at midday, did you have that in the kitchen as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes. And tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your father come home for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes, and tea. Eight o'clock was our suppertime always. When the work was done and - and then we used to have supper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 At dinnertime do you all eat together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes. OH we had all our meals together, although we had our separate rooms, my husband and I, but - we had me
als all together. Well it was nice, and the dog, we always had the dog with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Can you remember what you used to have at dinnertime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh just - just the ordinary, meat and - and vegetable, and a pudding. Always a pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You had tea, what time did you have tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Half past four. And supper at eight. Anything else? You won't have anything else to do today will you? Are you married, excuse me?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Can I ask you a bit more about meals again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What did you have for tea, can you remember the sort of things you used to have at teatime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well it was always bread and butter and - jam and marmalade or honey, and always cake, homemade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 And your father came home for that too did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes. He never had much tea, he jus
t wanted a cup of tea at - he very seldom had anything to eat, liked a good dinner, and a good supper and you see that was why we always had it at eight o'clock so that it'd have time to digest, and it wouldn't have done to gone }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9926461\charrsid5728063 to bed - 'cos he was asthmatic}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063  you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You all ate supper together did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes. Well we had our meals all together, the dog and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you have those in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Do you remember what sort of thing you had for suppers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well that varie
d. Mother and I were fond of bread and cheese, but generally father and George had - cold meat and - I think what father likes better than anything was a cold new potato.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your mother make her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. All her cakes and pastry and every
 - what I - what she didn't make I did. But oh that was a pity when the bakeries was done. I said to Mrs Wiggins, young Mrs Wiggins, whose father-in-law - that was his bakery you see, oh I says Hilda what I'd give for a slice of - off those little tin loa
ves I used to have. She said, you're not the only one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did she make her own jam or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes, all her own jams and pickles and - they don't do it now do they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Where did the fruit come from, from your garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, we bou
ght most of it and then you see well very often when father and my husband did work people would offer them fruit. You know, they - over done with it and - then as I said the other day I said when you think now - what they have to pay for sugar, let alone
 the fruit, and then there's - if people have got it cook it, there's all the gas and electricity, that's going to make jam dear you know. Isn't it. Don't think I'm mercenary. You have to look at these things don't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What sort of pickles did she make, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Cabbage - and onions - and walnuts, but we were none of us very keen on walnuts. But - my brother he was a - mark on pickled cabbage, Henry was. Then he would never eat a bit of meat. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did she make any wine, homemade wine?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, we were all teetotal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9926461\charrsid5728063 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 ers. Oh yes. Oh yes. No, there was no wine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Any medicine or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Medicine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your mother make any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh no. I used to massage father - don't put this in, in the - I used to start his be
droom fire - about the first week in October, and very often that was on 'til the end of May. Then three times a week I generally massaged his chest in between the blades with a special cream I made myself, a - a nurse gave me the prescription, I used to 
make it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What was it made of, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes, camphorated oil - camphor and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9926461\charrsid5728063 Vaseline}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 . I used to make that. He never had anything else. I don't hold with - I told the doctor the other day, he said something about me having to have this - I 
said, no I shan't - I - I want to die a natural death, I don't want any of your tablets. Didn't kick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your father grow any vegetables in the garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes, we'd got a nice vegetable garden. But my husband was the one that - father wasn't a 
keen gardener, but my husband was, both with flowers and vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When did your husband come to live in the house, what year would that be, can you remember how old you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 He was nineteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 That's when he came to live here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 That's when he came to live here, and he was - seventy-nine when he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What year was he born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Couldn't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How old were you when he came to live here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How old was he? Nineteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How old were you when he came to live here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well round about sixteen I suppose. Yes. Yes. I found him dead you know \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 the kitchen floor. Mm. Oh there's been some ups and downs but it hasn't turned out bad at the finish, I'm not quarrel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9926461\charrsid5728063 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
ing with it. But he thought it out, I don't want anything too personal. I don't know why I told you, only you kept asking me questions.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your family keep any animals, a pig or hens or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Ay what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Pigs or goats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, no, we'd got the two horses and the pony, that's all, and always a dog. And two cats. That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you have meat everyday sometime during the day for your food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Only dinnertime. Oh father and George had some in - as a rule at suppertime but mother and I didn't. My brother never touched meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you ever get a rabbit or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes, I used to be very fond of a rabbit. I shouldn't want it now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your father get that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh no, mother and I had to see to that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Where did your father get it from, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 The rabbit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Oh we - there was a shop in the town you see where they sold them, at the fishmongers or an odd shop, well I had to get it you see. And of course then they skinned them and cut them up and all, I was very amused the o
ther day - a young newly wed went int' the butchers and she had her meat an}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9926461\charrsid5728063 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
 - she said, well now I want some gravy. I wonder what the butcher thought. Yes, she wanted some gravy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your mother or you ever have to go a bit short so the men who were working or the children could have anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
We never went short. It was a plain living but we were never short, and mother never believed in going in for the cheapest. She says it doesn't pay in the long run.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Were you allowed to talk at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Yes. As a rule, but - of course father and my husband generally talking about the work, mother and I was waiting on 'em so of course woman like, and - oh yes, we were never restricted in any way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Not even when you were very small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Before your husband came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
I suppose I was always rather on the quiet side and - of course my greatest delight in those days was my dolls. They used to say I'd had a small fortune for - spent on dolls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When you were a child could you have a
nything you wanted to eat or did you have to have a piece of everything in the meal and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Oh no. I was a poor feeder. No, it was just a plain wholesome food. No, they - I was never faddy, 'cos - well it used to be a job to get me to eat I suppose sometimes, I don't trouble now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Could you leave food on the plate or would you get into trouble if you did that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What, told - in me young days? Oh no, sit up at the table and have it on a plate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 If you left any food on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Oh no, I wasn't forced to eat it if I didn't want it, that was it. Mother used to say it's no good forcing it my child if you can't eat it. And she never did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Could you ask for more if you wanted it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes. I did, but they didn't ever happen. I never wanted more, I never wanted much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Were you taught by your mother and father to sit up at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes, always sit up at the table. Father was very faddy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What about holding your knife and fork, did you have to hold those in a special way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes. And - father - and my brother would have their own special knife and fork and spoon and nobody else had to use it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did they have a special place at table, did you always sit in the same places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes. Yes. Father s
at one end. And - I sat the other, mother generally sat facing me and my husband - facing her you see. Just the four of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Were you allowed to bring your toys to the table when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I had to put 'em away. Of course, that's the mist
ake nowadays. People - children are not taught to tidy as they go are they. Well in the main, I don't know - I never had a lot to do with children and yet I think - I've often thought about it. My schoolteacher - she says you know, they wanted me to go in
 
for teaching you see - well - there was or two reasons, in the first thing we were dissenters, and the church people of course don't often make teachers of dissenters. That was one thing. And later on they said to me, you know Ethel, you ought to get into
 a gentleman's nursery, that would be your forte, well I thought that's funny - both cases be with children yet I've never been used to 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you have to ask to get down from the table or could you get down whenever you liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I got down when I'd finished, off in the garden amongst my flowers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When you were a little girl, who served the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Mother. Mother, but father always did the carving. And - after he passed away - I said to my husband, now, I said, George, you must do it. No, he says, I shan't, you must do it. I had to. Men - men do want some waiting on don't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I know how he felt, I can't carve. Can't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh I could. How wasteful. And your wife, oh she was silly to learn. Very silly. Yes. So you see - it's a cas
e of a woman, she has to do the shopping and the cooking and the carving, I don't call that fair you know, but then women have never had a fair deal all through life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I like to cook.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You like to cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I shouldn't have minded in some ways being a chef in a hotel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
How nice. Like my husband's father - he - he - he was a lovely cook. Mm. And where he lived they used to have parties at some castle, well it was Dedonton really. And he - he always did all the cooking - for those parties. Now 
father, he didn't have nothing to do with cooking. \{BLANK\} That's an old bake}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9926461\charrsid5728063 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
house you know. Well see there was the bakery - there and here you know. Because I had the over - 'til filled in because I got an idea that the nice come in from the garden. Yes, it's a nice garden. I love it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 It's a nice old fashioned house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes, it is. I shouldn't say thank you for those that are built today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I live in an old house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You do? I don't like these put up with - con - I hate concerts, 'cos plenty of 'em are. Aren't they? Then there's a big cellar. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 And your father used to keep his wagons and things in the yard there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh no, down the bottom of the - there was a shed and - all down there, where the - veh - vehicles was kept you see a
nd - oh - yes. We've had some happy times, we've had our ups and downs. There's some - when my friend died - my friends didn't think I should stay here alone. And I thought, well - it's one of two things. I've got to conquer - living here alone, or have s
o
meone else to live with me. And I had such a benefit of that I think no if I can master it I will. And I have. We had seven deaths in the house. Yes. Still I mastered it and I've been so glad. I said to Doctor Bradden - I was talking to him about it and w
e
ll that was before he gave in you see, you taking that down - he was talking and I said well Doctor, I said, my point is this, I said, if you had anyone in the house you have an added responsibility, I says, it doesn't matter whether you had 'em as a boar
der or a tenant or a help, and I said, I think I've had enough. He says, my and I think you have, he says, and you're one of those people that would be better alone. Because, he says, you've got some good friends. I've never regretted it. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I think you're right to stay in your own house and where you know people had where you've been it seems sensible to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 It's surprising though, Mrs Wiggins - young - you don't know her I expect. Young Mrs Wiggins, she says, it's - she comes in, oh so and so a
sked after you, today. Oh, I says, I didn't know they knew I was alive now. So she says, they do. And - but - the head nurse, she says, whatever you do Mrs Morgan, don't give up your home. She says, somebody'll look after you but don't let your home go. N
o
, I says, I don't meant to if I can help it. I've seen so much of it. And it was left to me and I think I must take care of it. Just the same as they say, oh why don't you have your hair off, I said, no, my mother taught me to take care of my hair, it'll 
s
top as long as I can. Well but it was a funny thing, I'd been up here three - three years come November, and I was just getting a few grey hairs, which didn't bother me, but since I've been here you see it's gone white. I don't mind a bit. I sit out at ni
ght for half an hour and then that's when I do it, I don't like the nurses touch it. So that's what I do, it keeps my fingers - a bit you see. And - so I says, no, I shan}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9926461\charrsid5728063 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 t have it off. So that's that. So I - I came to that conclusion and I've never regretted it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Can I talk to you a bit more about your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Yes. I can't tell you much more though. I don't feel weary, but you please yourself. But - do you know which day you'd come? Because that friend that came in now, she comes Tuesday afternoon -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When you were a child was your mother an easy person to talk to did you get on all right with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Mother was a very quiet disposition. Very deep. But mother and I were one you know always. 'Course father was - more hasty. Someone said to -
 to mother one day when they started - with the electric you know, they - mother - father didn't have it, he - he was going to have it and then by the time they got round to us the people began to squeal about the expense. Oh well, he says, if that's it w
e
 shall have to wait a bit that's all. And - I heard someone say to mother one day, I wonder you know Mrs Morgan you don't have the electric. Yes, she says, what with Ethel and her father I got quite enough electricity in the house. At present. It wasn't v
ery complimentary to us was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 It depends how you take it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Well it does. But that's the answer she made, she'd got quite enough with Ethel and her father, but mother was very quiet, you never saw mother put herself out much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 But could you talk to her if you had any worries when you were a little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh we never had anything apart, not mother and I. We were one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What about your father, did you get on all right with him, could you talk to him when you were a little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Wel
l, father was a sterner disposition. And I think - oh we always got on you understand, but - that - after mother passed away I think father and I got closer than we ever had, you see, he was dependent on me for everything. That's where it was
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them, did they expect you to show them respect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes, we were taught that in those days, not as they are today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How did you show respect to your parents, do you know, how did you behave towards them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Well - I knew very well what I could and what I couldn't do, and they always trited to give me all the pleasure I could because of course - well they used to reckon I used to have a month at school and at home a fortnight under the doctor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you call them mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Oh yes - no, it was mother - yes, mother and father. I like that. I said the other day - a friend of mine, she got a - grandchild, I said, for heavens sake don't start that nanna business. I says, why can't parents tea
ch their children to say mother. I said, I think it's the loveliest word in the English language. I don't object so much to daddy. But I think mother should have her rights.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your parents bring you up to behave in a certain way to your brother, or special way towards your brother, and to other children?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I haven't any other children you see, there was only Henry, and he was - very precious to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What about other children, not in your family, if one of them hit you in the street say, would
 your parents say that you should hit another back if they hit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
No. I never got amongst a crew like that. That was my brother - there, and he and father went to Teignmouth for their summer holiday, and that was took there and he was taken ill a w
eek after he came home so I couldn't have had a later photo of the boy. Yes. Father and - yes. That's mother's mother and father taken on their golden wedding day at the old gasworks, where I spent the happiest hours of my childhood. Yes, that's all down 
now you see. And that is my own father and mother - their golden wedding day, under the arch in the garden, the arch that I trained, the clematis. I don't want for any - oh it's raining.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What kind of person do you think your parents would have liked you to grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Mm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What sort of things did your parents hold important in life, what sort of person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Truth and honesty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You said that you were dissenters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Was that very important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes, it was. We were Method
ist, my father was a Methodist local preacher. And my mother was in the Sunday school - the last Sunday of her life, it was a bitter cold day. You're not taking this down are you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What did your parents think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Ah you never heard a swear word in my home. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What did they think of other people that did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
They didn't say much. We had - my husband bought a - somebody in the day - one day to tea. He began, I said, excuse me but we're not used to that language in our home. George gave me such a look but he didn't say anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When you were a little girl and your mother and father were talking to grown ups were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. I was there but I didn't have to interrupt. Ah we were taught pret - different 
in those - I pity the children today. Are you paid for all the time you sit and talk? I daresay Doctor Badden will say - he - I don't know - I thought it was very nice of him to come in to know if I minded, I said, you know I don't mind. Well the nurses -
 
one of the nurses, I shouldn't like this now - she come in and I've had some nice talks, she says, do you know - my husband says he should like to come and see you. She says, I told him no good thinking that, you didn't like men in your bedroom. I shan't 
have to tell her I've had one shall I?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You've had two, you've had Doctor Badden too,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Oh I don't take any notice of him. I don't take no notice. He's not the doctor when he's on a private visit. He's sociable. He's homely you know, and he drops - 
well you don't see that professional - he hasn't got his stick, I - of course he's got hip trouble you see. Mm. 'Cos we had a discussion about it once, he said, on about me having an operation, I says, I'm not going to have an operation to please anybody,
 
I says, once you get the knife in you don't know where it's going to end, I says, and - I've made up my mind - that I'll fight - and I have. I says, I'm not going to give in to that. And he says, you've done well you know, I said, yes. We was talking abou
t it only the other day when he came in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Can you remember when you were a little girl if you were naughty or if you did something your parents thought was naughty what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Only talk to me quietly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You were never punished at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. Never. No. Love had to do it in those days didn't it. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Would you say that when you got a bit older did you get the ideas about how to behave from your father or your mother or from both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Both. Mother was very well behaved. You see father was a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9926461\charrsid5728063  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 fi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9926461\charrsid5728063 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
hter. One of our doctors that was here - he - I don't suppose you remember - you ever heard his name, Doctor Caldwell. He tried his hardest to talk father into - writing a book, he says, I know you could do it. It - with your different exper
iences you've had. And another friend of mine, one of the Mrs Banbury's, she says, pa, do do it, she says, I'll help you, and she could have done, but we couldn't get father on it. No, he says, he wouldn't, of course he never had any schooling you see. An
d yet - not having any schooling he persevered in business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did he teach himself to read and write?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
I suppose he learnt that at - what little bit of schooling he had but he did all his own booking, correspondence and - and that you know. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Can you remember when you had a birthday when you were a little girl, would it be a special day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
No, never went in for parties, there was always presents. I was never strong enough for anything of that in those days, no excitement you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you have special food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I forget.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What about Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Oh - we loved our Christmas. The earlier years you see there was father and mother and I and my brother - and my mother had a sister and her husband and two children - and our Christm
as Day was always down at the gas house, dinner, tea and supper, we've had some lovely times there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When did you get your presents, in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 In the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 And then you went down to the gas works?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 We went to dinner, tea and supper and of course Uncle John was single and he got his piano and - he was a good musician and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 And you all sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Mm? Yes, we all had carols and - oh yes. Then eleven o'clock grandpa and uncle had to clear off to put the lights out. And mother 
and I and - father generally stayed down there with grandma until grandpa come home at eleven o'clock.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you have any musical instruments in the house when you were a girl, here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I had my piano when I was sixteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You played that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your father play any instrument?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. Neither did mother. Father was a very good singer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When did he sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh we had our Sunday nights and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you have family prayers on a Sunday night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. No. We had our Bibles and we all went to chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 But you used to sing on a Sunday night? When would that be, after supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Yes. George was a very - my husband was a very good singer, well I suppose all the Morgan - the men - of the family, I mean father's brothers and that, of course they was Welsh descent you know. They was all fond of singing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What sort of things did he sing on a Sunday night, hymns?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 And other sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Just religious songs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes, that's it. But - no - my - one
 of my friends, she's one of the Mrs Banbury's, she used to sit in front - of my brother at chapel, oh she says, I do love to hear - listen to Nenry singing, I think his voice is lovely. Yes, I say, it's nice to have happy memories.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Do you remember your parents playing games with you at all at home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. No. No, we were fond of reading you know and - I was always got sewing on the go, shirt making or something. For 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When did you start doing your sewing, how old were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I was sixteen when I went out in the workroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 But you sewed at home before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Oh yes. But - father bought me my sewing machine then you see, yes. I did all the shirt making and - clothes and that. I didn't have much leisure time. When I got any leisure time it was out in the garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your father read a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Mother was a reader. Oh she - she - and what puzzled me with mother you know, if people were talking in the room she could go on reading, it wouldn't interfere - but I couldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What sort of things did she read, books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh - Jane Eyre and Mrs Henry Woods and - and - well, it - what's this on here now, her books and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Charlotte Bronte?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes. Oh all those. Mrs Henry Woods. And - oh I've got one or two of her old books, but my favourite books are Ethel Dell's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your father read at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Not a lot. Didn't get on beyond - beyond the newspaper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What newspaper did you have, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh we had the Weekly Echo, the Oxford - well there weren't the papers in those days. About two a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You had the Oxford paper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 And the Methodist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Which Oxford paper did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oxford Times and Chronicle. Mm. We was talk - I was talking to - one of those two two friends of mine that - talk
ing about the difference, I says, I was thinking only the other day, the difference in the Sundays now. Television to tempt people away from a place of worship. I says, there was no Sunday papers. No open shops that people could shop that day, and no ice}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9926461\charrsid5728063  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 c
ream barrows. No, she said. And I said, there was the letter in the paper only this week, some woman said - there was no peace now on Sunday afternoon for these ice cream barrows, couldn't something be done to stop it for we get no rest. To book a seat in
 that chapel before it was quite finished.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 That was the United Chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
That was the United Methodist. My husband was - my - my - my husband and I were - I think we were the last two married in that chapel. And I think - the funeral service was the last one - at my father's funeral.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When you were a child do you remember any funerals in the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, because I never - I wasn't allowed to see them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Children weren't allowed to the funerals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I wasn't. I was highly strung you se
e. You see, after my brother died - three months after I went down with a breakdown and that same - Scotch nurse that was with him was here with me for sometime. And she told me when she left me, she says, well I didn't think you know I was going to put y
o
u on your feet. She says, I may as well tell you now. But still there it is, I got nothing to grumble about now. So you see, that's - that - chapel the Wesleyan, goes in the name of Methodist but I says never to me, but you see after that, I went into the
 Baptist, and I played the instrument round there - for seven years three times a week, and they're the ones you see that come to me now. It's a nice little chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Can you remember going visiting outside, did you go visiting to see neighbours or friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, not very often. I had one or two old friends I used to see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 This is when you were a child? Did your parents take you visiting at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. No. As I grew older there was - three or four old people I used to visit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 That was from the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, no, on me own. On me own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I was going to ask you about being taken shopping but I know about that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I had to do that on me own. You wouldn't catch mother going shopping. She gave us all education, and I always got on with t
he shopkeepers so it didn't matter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Do you remember going out alone with your father at all when you were a little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When I was in the trap with him, and - sometimes we went for a walk on a Sunday. We generally all went together on a Sunday 
night after service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Where did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Generally along the Green Lane, I wasn't a lover of the park. It's too much you mustn't do this and you mustn't do that, I like the green lanes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you go on outings any other time, on Bank Holiday Monday or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. I didn't like a crowd. I used to like to go to our flower show. That was lovely. Of course that fell through.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your father not approve of Bank Holiday crowds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh - he didn't mind, but you see he was quiet, he didn'
t go about much. Our friend come in one night and she said, doesn't Mr Morgan or your husband go out at night? I said, no, they work too hard all day to want to go out at night. I said, they like their fireside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. Never. Only about twice. But I couldn't travel you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How old were you when you went away first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh I don't know. First holiday mother and I had we went to Birmingham for a week, and we was glad to get home. Oh no, home was the best to 
me always. Anything else? I used to take father's and mother's breakfast up. And generally my husband's. Then the dog and I used to go out the back way along Green Lane. And when I came back mother always cooked on a Sunday in the winter but not in the su
m
mer, I used to go to morning school at ten o'clock, play for them. Then - we generally all went to chapel. In the summertime mind, not in the winter. And then in the afternoon, mother and I both went to Sunday school again, father and George was one in on
e room and one in another, having a nap. And then we all went to chapel at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Was that the same when you were a small child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes. Well of course I didn't go to Sunday school then. But that - go on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you have different clothes on a Sunday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes, we always had our best clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How long did best clothes last?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Ah - as long as we could make 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you play games on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. We had - mother always got as scripture puzzles. When we couldn't go out you see on - I didn't go out much at nights you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your parents think it was wrong to play on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Never thought about it, mother'd be - always got some - books and - puzzles, well we didn't have much time on Sunday what with the Sunday school and the services. And then once a month it was sacr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9926461\charrsid5728063 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 ment after the - after the service you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You used to go to the United Independent Methodist chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Not independent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Just United?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Just United.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How often did you used to go on a Sunday, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 To the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well we used to go twice on a Sunday, and then I once a week night service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 And you went to Sunday school as well, when you were a bit older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Ah yes, I had my girls, mother had her girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When did you start teaching there, when you were sixteen or younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Oh about sixteen or seventeen, but what always amused me with mother - she said she wouldn't have a class of girls, no, and I says I wouldn't have a class of boys
, 'cos I said there'd be trouble if I did. And the latter years one of the teachers said to mother - Mrs Morgan I do wish you'd have my girls, she says, they're getting beyond me. And mother fell into the trap, she had the girls, and somebody else had her
 senior boys, well I says, after all those years to take over a class of girls which you wouldn't have had on any account.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you go on a Sunday school outing at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Where did you used to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh one of the villages we used to go you see in farmers wagons then. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What did you do when you went on the outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh we had scrambles and races and - all that sort of thing you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you decorate the wagons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Mm? The horses and wagons and one night we ca
me home in a thunderstorm, horses nearly bolted. I said, I don't think I shall go again. But I did of course. And then you see - it's all been different since they broke up the Methodists and the - I have one of their - Methodists, Mrs - Mss Strong, you d
on't know her of course, she's getting on but - we don't touch on - chapel affairs 'cos we shouldn't agree.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How was your chapel different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 In what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You say you were the United?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 And there's the Wesleyan up here, how did you see them as different when you were a girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
I didn't recognise it you see, I didn't realize it, the - it's all the same mode of worship, now round at the Baptist you see they don't have infant baptisms. It's immersion. But there's - these have the 
christening here and all - but I don't know that - ministers and all are different now, they're not like they used to be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Why's that? How are they different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well - as I said in those days there was a local preachers. I said they worked hard six
 days a week - for a living, and they had to work then, I said, and Sunday they gives to God. But I said you see they went to the different villages, I said, there was no buses and motors to rush 'em about with, they had to find their own transport.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Do you remember any of those preachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh lots of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Who were they? What did they do for a living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Ah - now you've asked me, well there was my father, here, and there was the Banbury's you see and the Torrells.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What did the Torrells do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Torrels, they had that big shop you see. Mr. Torrell, his - family, they're a - nice family, four boys. One of 'em come in here last week, what did he come for? Brought me some flowers. And - but as I say you hadn't got the local preachers now
. It's all left to the ministers.-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Did you remember any other things you used to do with the chapel apart from the outing, did you have a Christmas concert or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes, yes. And a tea. Oh we had a lively time there. We used to 
take the children out you see for the summer treat and then we had the other in our schoolroom, beautiful schoolroom you know it was. And - oh it made some work, cake making and - cutting up and all the rest of it, but we did it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you belong to the choir at the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, I hadn't any voice to choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 But you played the piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Yes, we got the organ down there you see, and then round at the Baptist there is a - the Baptist organ is the one that my uncle played for years in t
he Methodist chapel, well then you see there was the break up and - we managed to get that organ, we had - what was it they - two years to pay for it. We played for it in six months. And I played it for seven years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Was there a temperance club at your chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
There used to be years ago, but then you don't hear of the Blue Tem - the Good Templars now the - I remember the time when the Good Templars always wore the blue ribbon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Were you a temperance person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I never had any drinks. Well none of us did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your father wear a blue ribbon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I don't remember it, I remember them talking about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you wear a blue ribbon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. But you see temperance was as big a thing with - with dissenters and chapel people as anything,
 but I don't know that there's so much of it now. I don't think that there is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your father preach at temperance meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I don't know that he preached at temperance meetings but he always preached. Oh yes, he was a local preacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did he preach at the big services on a Sunday afternoon in the Town Hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh no, nothing of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Just at the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 And one - the village chapels. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Was what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Grace, did you say grace before you had a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Yes. Yes. And down at the gas works when grandpa and grandma and this uncle lived there, grandpa always had morning prayer. Yes. Yes, but you see - times was alter you never knew when our people going out, father and - George
 was off and - out at four o'clock in the spring, when they got spring clean fever and I used to call it. Of course theres not so much of that done now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your father say grace at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Grandpa did - and mother. But - it was - wasn't so much time then, well - we had our quiet times but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What about prayers at night when you were a little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, well we all said our prayers at night, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your mother teach you them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 We had our own in our own room you see. Yes. That's a change for me to hear anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Before 1911 did your father take any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 YES? He was on the council one year. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Do you know what his views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, he was a Liberal I know that, but - oh yes, he was on the town council one year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When was that, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Oh I can't remember. He was that but mother said it wouldn't happen again. She'd see to that. Meetings was too late at night. I don't think he ever did stick up for it again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Was that before the great war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Yes. Oh that was a time, do you - oh of course you remember that don't you? You do don't you? Mm. Not the last war? I had three evacuees - and three -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You say your father was a Liberal, do you know did he ever say why he was a Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 \{BLANK\} I expect like a good many more. Yes. He never discussed politics much. I said politics - shouldn't be talked of in the pulpit.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Were they talked of in the pulpit do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Sometimes they have been. Still - got to live and learn haven't you,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Was your mother a Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes. All Liberals. Grandpa and Grandma. I'm watching very carefully - now, Jeremy Thorpe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Are you still Liberal then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes, I should be. Well if there was an election now I shouldn't vot
e if I could, because I'm so disgusted with the Parliaments. When you look back over the years and think of some of the men that I can remember and see what we got now - you look at Gladstone, that's his photo over there, and some of the rest of 'em and s
ee what's there now I wouldn't go over the door sill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Is that your father's picture of Gladstone?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, that's mine. A friend gave it me. Friend that was leaving Woodstock. She says, you'd better have this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your father have pictures of people like Gladstone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Oh no, no, but she was leaving Woodstock and she says - I'll leave this with you. Well it's been very interesting hasn't it? We haven't run anybody down much have we. I mean - carefully watching Jeffrey - Jeremy Thorpe. I'm glad he's married again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Do you remember sometimes men felt that they risked losing their job or their livelihood if they voted Liberal, do you know if your father ever knew about anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I don't think so. No. I remember - my husband tell
ing me once about his father, he was working at some house, and the lady of the house was deploring - what a hold the middle class had got now, they didn't seem to have any respect. And uncle said, no, well, he says, I think if you look at your Bible, at 
a
 certain place, you'll see it says the time will come when the meek will inherit the earth, her says, that's what's started. I could - I could hear uncle saying it in that quiet way. Yes, he says, you'll see - that's what you'll find and that's what's sta
rting now. Do you think so?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I hope so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 So do I. Well you've learnt a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Was your father actually in the Liberal party, was he a member of the party in Woodstock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes, he was a Liberal and he went into the council as a Liberal you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did he work at election times for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Oh no, he wasn't educated up to that. You see he had no education, never went to school after he was seven but - I sometimes think - it was a wonderful life, well - they tell me, one or two says you have
 got a clear brain. Well that's where I've inherited it from. I don't know that it was any different to anybody else but I've had th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9926461\charrsid5728063 at thrown at me once or twice l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 ately.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Were most of the chapel people Liberals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes. Liberal and temperance, bu
t I don't think now - a lot - well I don't say they're not temperance, but then - they scoffed at the idea of anything in the way of strong drink, but I don't think there's many like it today. I don't really. We never had it in our home, well we did have 
i
t in our home at once, that's another little bit, father had - used to have a terrible bad foot - I don't know what it was but it used to go in cracks up his ankle and how he kept on work I don't know. Well every winter - that come back and he was under o
u
r local doctor. And finally somebody suggested that he went to a specialist in London. And he went, and he was a Jew. He had to go once a month, and he'd have a bottle of stuff to - bathe it, oh and I can smell that stuff now. And a bottle of medicine to 
t
ake, once a month. And at the end of the time this - Jew asked father what his position was as regards work. He says, it doesn't matter what my position is, I don't want any - anything different to other people, I can pay for it. But he was to have a glas
s
 of beer every night for his supper. And of course that rather upset mother and my father, so what do you think Henry went and did? He went and bought a pint glass so that father shouldn't have more than his - and that glass is hanging in the kitchen now,
 at least I don't know whether any of 'em have broken it, I don't think they have. Yes, so that he was sure and not have more.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I asked you about your father's politics. Was your father a member of any political party do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Was he a member? He was a Liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did he work at election time, help the party, help the Liberals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, I don't think so. He was a - he was on the - council here you know, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh I don't know, a good many years ago. I only 
know mother told him it would never happen again. 'Cos their meetings was on too late at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your father - he was on the council?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How often did he have to go to meetings of the council?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well you see, when they had an electi
on and there was fresh coun - councilors - they had pretty frequent meetings, just at the beginning I suppose to think get - get things organised and that you know, but it - it wasn't very - often after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How long was he on the council for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Only the one year. I said - mother wasn't going to have it again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Would that be before the first world war?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 So it was when you were a little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes, I wasn't very old then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When your father and mother weren't working how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When your father finished work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Oh well by the time father gave in you see he was an asthmatical subject, and then you see my husband carried on. See father and my husband was in partnership you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What about when he was still at work, in the evenings, what did he do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Stayed in. A friend came in one days, and she said, Mrs Morgan, doesn't - Mr Morgan and your husband go out in the evening? No, I said, they don't, I said, they works hard all day and the fireside and a paper was quite enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What about your mother, did she have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. Nothing. The only interest outside the home was the Sunday school. That's all we were home lovers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 So your father never went out in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
No. Never. Oh well of course - he was in the fire service for a good many - I've got two long service medals of his. And - the only time my husband did go out you see they had a social club, and sometime
s after supper he'd go round there for an hour, that was all. Door - door was always locked at ten o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Your father was in the fire service was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes, father was one of the first firemen, belonged to them - it first started you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 So he'd go out for a bit some evenings to the social club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Not father, my husband. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 But your father wouldn't even do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. He sat - well, hardworking you see and in that time they was up at four o'clock in the morning when people 
had got the spring cleaning fever, 'cos as I used to term it, well of course now - there isn't the chimney sweeping now. 'Cos people go in for electric and central heating. I was talking to someone the other day - about chimney sweeping, and they said, oh
 
well you see, there's not chimney sweeping needed now. The - central heating. I said, for goodness sake don't get that idea, I says, sweeps - are needed now, I said, why they were - on the wireless one night there was an appeal for chimney sweeps. People 
couldn't get them you see. So I said, don't get that idea.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your father take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, he was no sportsman. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did he belong do you know to any savings club or friendly society?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. Don't think that. I tell you we were stick at homes. We loved our home. It was always enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 As a child who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Well you see - up to I was about twelve years old it was a case of - month at school and a fortnight at home bad, so that - well we were talking the ot
her days and I said you see I had that disadvantage as a child, I could never go out and about and with other children, but for all that I'd always got a special chum, you see, and very often she'd come in in - in home here with me in the evening and I mi
ght go into her home, they lived just a few doors off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You had your brother as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Well of course I was ten when Henry came. I didn't want anything else when I got him. He was my all. We was laughing about it the other day. And - of course one 
of my pet aversions is Liz Burton, and they've only got to - to mention - Liz Burton and they say she's got it, but - Henry could never pronounce Ethel. So mother - said why don't you say Liz. And the only time I'd done anything that I knew he didn't like
 it was Ethel, otherwise it was always Liz. I says, I shouldn't answer to it now for anybody you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Whereabouts did you play when you did play outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Where did - oh up and down this pavement here, used to have hopscotch and skipping - we were safe then you know with no traffic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 But when you weren't too good you'd play indoors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes, and I'd always got a whole shoal of dolls. I loved my dolls.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Whereabouts did you play, in your room or in the kitchen or where?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 In the ki
tchen we had, and father and - mother would perhaps be in the other. Mother you know - used to do a lot of rope knitting. Rugs you know. Just for our own use you see. And I'd always got plenty of needlework you see. I was never in want of a job. Perhaps t
hat was as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You used to play hopscotch and skipping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes, good for the shoes. Hopscotch and skipping, I was never very interested in marbles. Or cricket.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Do you remember any other games you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes, if it was a wet day we u
sed to sit inside the door - on the mat and play dabs. Do you remember - I don't suppose you know that, little pebbles you see and you threw them and caught them. I said you - young people don't know the fun we had in simple days - days gone by. I said th
e
 other day I said oh you don't see the children with hoops and - hoops and stocks and skipping ropes and that sort of thing. And really it - it was healthy exercise. But - as we were saying the only day - other day, my friend and I, well she says, even th
e children have to be taken to school and fetched home when they should be walking because - I quite think myself so}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9926461\charrsid5728063  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
much of this thrombosis is the children having ex - not having exercise. Don't you? Then you don't know so far back as that. No. Oh no, I th
ink that's the cause of a lot of thrombosis now. That was my husband's - and then you see chimney sweeping was hard work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, I was too particular for that. They used to say if I got a spot nobody didn't have any rest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Were you allowed to play with who you liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, I picked my own friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your parents have anything to say in who you played with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. Oh of course you see, as I say the one or two friends I had - they'd come
 in her or I went into their home, they knew who I was with. But you get plenty to amuse you in the country. But what I liked best was to take the dog and go along the green lanes, that was the nicest. I pity the children that can't do that now. They can 
learn such a lot in nature. Don't you think? Yes, they do. I don't think you know - taken on the whole, children today have such a happy time as we did. You see, they're always wanting something fresh. Why even the other day D}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9926461\charrsid5728063 octor Bedden was talking, he sai}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
d, people don't seem as if they can settle in one place long now do they? I said, no, they want to move all the time. He's very free and easy. I mean - now he isn't a doctor, well you know what I mean, he doesn't practice, he - he hasn't got the doctor's 
manner when he comes in. Mm. You taking all that down? Ay?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your parents ever say you can't play with that child or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you belong to any youth organisations at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. No, we - we had a - Christian Endeav
our but belonging to our chapel and - I didn't want to go out in the evening, and my mother never did. I don't think mother ever went out from Sunday 'til Sunday, she was quite content. Well then the last six years of grandma's life she lived with us you 
see. There was alwa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9926461\charrsid5728063 ys somebody to be looked after.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
What about when you were still at school, I know you didn't go to school very much, but what did you do in the evenings when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well, at home, I - I say I'd got - crochet work or knitting or something of that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How old would you be when you started that, knitting and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh I don't know. I seemed always interested in - in the - well when I couldn't get out they get me plenty of wool and I could be 
knitting and crocheting different things, they never - so I never left - lost - it never went heavy with me you know. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you have any other hobbies, did you collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you have any pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Any what? Pets? I got me ca
ts and me dog and - there was three horses in the stable and I loved them all, that was a big loss to me, my animals, we'd always got animals. We had three cats as a rule.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You did a lot of gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes, I loved me garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When you were a little girl did you have your own bit of garden?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes. But - the two things I should have liked - was a greenhouse - and - a good amount, I should like that. Still that wasn't to be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You said you went for walks along the Green Lenes with your dogs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How far did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh, just all depend how soon I got tired.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Whereabouts did you go from Woodstock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Out over that gate and along the Green Lane. I used - Sunday morning, of course that was after we were marr
ied, I used to get up in good time Sunday morning and I'd have father and mother's breakfast up to them and I took my - husband's to him and I used to say come on Dash, and we used to go - along Green Lane, and at the bottom of the lane there was a lovely
 tree. It's down now they tell me, I sayd it would be if it was anything nice. And we generally stayed under that tree - and listened to the chimes - of Sunday morning, it was lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you have a bicycle at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. No, nothing of that and when my husband had the car I never went out in it if I could help it. I was nervous.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you do any sports when you were a girl at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What about going out, did you ever go to the theatre?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. I've never been to a theatre, I've never been to a dance. But I was perfectly happy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What did your parents think about theatres?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Well of course - it would - they never took any interest in anything of that. Of course we had the wireless. And - so there was always something to li
sten to. Do you hear the community singing Sunday night? Oh it was lovely. Oh there's plenty, I always look forward to Sunday with the wireless.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When you were still a little girl did you ever get any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. Father used to buy so much 
sweet for me Saturday night, and they had to last. And you s-e in those days - it was no use asking for ha'pennies and pennies because they weren't available.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did anybody outside your home help your mother with the house or family, neighbours or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
No. We always had a wash woman. And - oh I don't know - first one I remember, she was here fifteen years, and the next was fourteen years and the last was - twenty-seven years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How often did she come in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Every week. Every week for w
ashing and Saturday to help with the cleaning, but I didn't want help with cleaning I liked housework. I loved the housework. And father and my - husband used to say I was never happy - happier than when I'd got some place upside down. Well, I says, there
's always a place left for you to sit in comfortable so why's it matter. If it helped me - does me good. I didn't let them have it all their own way you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What would have happened when y-ou were a little girl if your mother had been ill, who would have helped done the house and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Who would have come, there was always someone would come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, we never had a lot of neighbours. Mother wasn't one you see to encourage it. She was quite content, but then you see father - 
was very good in the home. Of course her last illness - she was only ill for four days. And - well there's always been someone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Do you remember what happened when your brother was born? Did you help then about the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well you see I was but t
en, but we were talking the other day about some of the girls seem so - no idea of housework, well I says, from the time the boy was born, I says, I always felt I must do all I could to help mother, and one thing mother would never do and that was shoppin
g. I did the shopping. And I - of course she wrote a lot of it down. But she says it's not good my child, if you can't go they'll have to go without, I can't go, and she never would. She was a shy disposition you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you have any relatives living in Woodstock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes. Father's - father, lived in Old Woodstock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What did he do?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Well chimney sweeping. And then - when he was taken ill - mother had him with us, that was in a house up the street, I think he lived a month. Then father ha
d one brother, he worked at Belenheim. And that was all. Big family but of course they was all scattered. But father you see was the only one to stay in Woodstock - of the family. He had plenty of callers one time and another but - plenty in the house one
 time and another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What about the people who lived at the gas works?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Who, grandma and grandpa? Oh they were lovely. Think the happiest - that's their photo up there, taken on their golden wadding day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How much did you see of your grandma and grandpa?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Oh I nearly lived down there. See I was the first grandchild. And it was a lovely comfortable warm little home you know. Fifty years grandpa and uncle was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You'd go down there on your own would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes, I'd go down ther
e on my own. I was - we was talking to - whatever were we talking about, something about the apple picking, well I said, they got - they had two lovely apple trees down at the gas works, and - they was always picked fair day, first day in October, and the
n we went - grandchildren went down there to tea you see, it was quite a red letter day. But it was hard work you know in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What about your parents friends? Did they have lots of friends in Woodstock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, not outside our own community. 
You see there was the chapel work and we was all - united then. And we always had enough interest in each other. A strong churchman was in here one day, and he said - oh dear, he says, I don't know why it is but you Methodists, he says, you all hang toget
her, he says, their joys and sorrows are all one. He says, you don't find it in the church. But all that's altered now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How often did they see the chapel friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Mm? Oh we always mixed together you see. We had our services on Sunday and the Sund
ay school and a - service in the week and then there was the Christian Endeavours, that was the young people you see. Of course the Banbury's was the chief - ones. There was a lot of them round but they're all gone you see, except these up at London House
 
now. Still as I say that's one blessing I've got today, it's the memories. And I can go through it all. The young people of today you know, they're not going to have a happy memories that we had, I don't think. They might, but I can't see it. Because you 
see - we had to be content with the simple pleasures That's what I mean. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your mother have any friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, of course there was grandma and grandpa at the gas works, but mother never branched out. Chapel friends - people were 
all friends you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your father have friends that were just his friends really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well yes, one or two, but as I say they - they was busy all day and they didn't go out at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Where did your father see the friends that were just his own, or where would he have gone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Well - there was a saddle maker and harness maker up the street, and they were cronies, they were in the fire service together. And he was always at work and sometimes - at night after father had had his supper, he sa
id, I think I'll go and have half an hour with - with a neighbour, and it was in his wife's workroom that I was you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Were your parents friends ever invited into your parents home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Were what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Were your parents friends ever invited into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Not - not a lot 'cos we generally gone - relatives or somebody here. Living here with us you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How often, have you got any idea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Would the friends be invited in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh they weren't invited in, they dropped in any time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 If somebody dropped in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh be made welcome of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Would they get something to eat or drink offered them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes. But you see - I was just cooling down and then I had - what did I have first - oh a young girl with two babies, t
hey were the first that were put on me. And Jackie could play beautifully though. But if there was one word in the English language he did hate it was work. Now I said and I fancy you live up to it don't you? The other two were not so -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Would people come by when you were a girl, would people come by and visit on any special occasions or special days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Yes, one day in particular, I was fed up. I says, I'm not having anymore of this. Mother was just getting over the shingles and I was pretty tired.
 And I think - three different friends came in and I had to get tea. I said to mother, I'm not going to have any more of this. So the bank - it was - it was August Bank Holiday you see, next August Bank Holiday I quietly - drew the front curtains down and
 
let the latch down. We sat - we was in the middle room. I says, I - don't want any more of that. See, a lot of people to go out and about and we were took unawares at holiday time and we always looked for those days for a bit of a rest, I didn't get any t
hat day. I thought, I'm not having it again. They never said don't do it, knew it was no good 'cos I was going to do it and that was it. We had a lovely quiet day. We weren't a bit tired at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When would that have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 That was one August Ba
nk Holiday some years ago. And I'd had a pretty bad time with mother, she'd had shingles. And the - beauty of it was she just got over it and my - my husband had it. I didn't have it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Would you say that the friends that came to your house, were invite
d into your house, were mainly your mother's friends or mainly your father's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Father's. You see, mother's - there was only grandpa and grandma and uncle at the gas works, that's all of mother's people. Well father's people didn't live in the town. But you know they gave you friendly call.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did people call in just without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Was that friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh just friends, anyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What about neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well we didn't have many neighbours. It was the - next do
or, Mr and Mrs Gas - Mr and Mrs Wiggins, that's the daughter-in-law that comes in you see, and - Whitlocks next door, I suppose you know the Whitlocks - heard of the Whitlocks. They run this cafe now. Mm. I don't know why that isn't open, hasn't been open
 for a week. No. We're not intimate but we're friendly, you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 People often tell us that people made their own entertainments in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What sort of things did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 In what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 If your parents had some friends in the house what do you think they did, did they play music together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Oh only sit and talk and might be at the piano, that was all. You see we had simple things in those days, we didn't go in - for parties and dances and theatres and all - the money didn't run to it in those days you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Many people divide society into social classes, or into groups.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 There wasn't that feeling in Woodstock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You wouldn't think so at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. That old friend of mine, she's older than I
 am, and she's - at Stonesfield now with her daughter. She said pretty well the last time I she said there isn't the old friendly feeling and neighbourliness that we used to know is there. I said, no, that's all gone now it's a new generation. And she say
s, of course we lived hard, we worked hard, and she said it was a plain living - but she says we wasn't brought up on - on the - chin stuff of - and frozen stuff, and fish and chips and ice cream. Well we - no, I said, we didn't. They're fresh people.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 So you wouldn't say there were any classes in Woodstock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
No, I don't think so. No snobbishness. There's more now I think. Well of course they're just a new generation. They're not brought up as we were. See - see what I mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Would you mix freely with all groups when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
It didn't matter to me who they were. Well you take Blenheim you see, we don't seem to hear much about Blenheim now. But then in those days each department has its own staff you see and - the upper servants woul
d associate with the trades people and - but you don't know nothing about 'em now. I can't find out what that last baby's name is at all. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You say the upper servants would associate with the trades people?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 They did in those days but you see 
they haven't any servants now as far as I can see. Of course they don't - he doesn't live at Blenheim, not the Duke.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Who would the lower servants associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Mm - amongst theirselves I suppose, there was always plenty there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What would you call trades people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well the people at the shops and that sort of things, you - there was the butchers and the drapers and - grocers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Were you trades people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well our father would have been called a tradesman you see, he was a tradesman. He - he left school I suppose at eight years of age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What sort of class would you think, you say there were trades people, would Church of England clergymen mix with trades people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 They did in those days but - you don't see anything of this rector now. I was having it out with Miss Strong the other day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What about the teachers in the school, would they mix with trades}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9926461\charrsid5728063 -}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh they was all right in those days, but nobody knows much about them now, you see they got these new school
s and that, it - there was one for the boys, one for the girls, and the smaller one for the infants. Well heaven knows what they've got now or how many there are in it. I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Were you ever told to curtsey to anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. No, and if I was I shouldn't have done it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Was there anybody you ever called sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
No. We didn't have that in those days. No, I told you what that woman said to my uncle didn't I, about the meek. It was my husband's father - and he was at la - some lady
's house, I suppose he was gas fitting, and this lady was deploring the way the middle class was taking the upper hand. And didn't pay enough respect to the upper class. So he says, well madam, he says, if you read your Bible, and look at a certain chapte
r, and a certain verse you'll see these words. The time will come when the meek will inherit the earth, and he says, that what they've started doing. Yes, she says, that's quite right.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Who do you think were considered the most important people in Woodstock in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
I couldn't say. You see, we hadn't a lot of big houses or anything of that. Oh I should be lost now, I shouldn't know where I was if I got outside the front door. They're all building round you know, they - they try to explain to me, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What sort of people went to the church, to the Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
I don't know, I suppose Blenheim people went and - and - that. I was saying the other day, I think I mentioned it, about the chapel in - in Blenheim did I? Well they ha
d their own private chapel, and - every Sunday afternoon all the servants were supposed to go. I said, the other days, I wonder what's become of that chapel because - it isn't used.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What sort of people went to chapels like yours, to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9926461\charrsid5728063 M}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 ethodist?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Trades people and - there was three or four of the families of the Banbury's you see and our own and other people. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did the farm labourers go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well some of them, but you see - well - there wasn't a lot of that class, you know what 
I mean. And you know in those days farm labourers hadn't much time for places of worship. There was cattle to be fed and - oh I haven't forgotten it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Where you lived, when you lived round here did all the trades}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9926461\charrsid5728063 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 people have the same sort of standard of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Oh yes. Yes. See - where we lived - before we came here - was that house just up the street where Mr Jerrams lived, and there was the grocers shop on either side, well there's only one grocers shop now is there. I don't know what t
hey've made of the other side. Is it a restaurant or something of that? So I was never dull, the - the - they always sort of encouraged me you see and mother knew where I was, you didn't worry mother. And yet I wasn't in there with the boys. Me father had
 a long illness, in fact he died of cancer, and the boys used to come in to us you see. Jack and Fred. Two nice lads they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Were some families in Woodstock thought of as rough and some respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. There's not much of that class about. Al
though I was saying only the other day you don't hear any drunks about at night now, so really I suppose they have got more select.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You say that a rough family would be one where there was a lot of drinking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I think so. 'Cos you don't hear of that now. Well I think \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 last two or three Christmas Eves - have been the quietest I ever knew because you see - there used to be the - men turning out of the public house and they was pretty lively sometime. But you don't hear nothing of that now,
 it's as quiet - well I suppose television holds the lot doesn't it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Do you remember any distinction between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, I don't think there was that spirit of - well - they was always - more friendly you see. Do you know I did
n't think I knew so much. It's bringing it out. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your father and mother have the same attitude to people of different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, it was all the same to mother, there's no snobbery about my mother. And of course father, he - he - he wou
ldn't be sat on, you know what I mean. Just as when somebody said to mother they - surprised they didn't have the electricity in, well - we were going to have it and then at the time it got round you see people were screaming so about - the coat, my fathe
r
 says, that must wait a bit then. And somebody said to mother one day, I am surprised you don't have the electricity. Well, she says, it's like this, between Ethel and her father I got quite enough electricity, and I - don't want any more. Very compliment
ary wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Do you think your mother saw herself as being part of a particular group or class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
No, no. You see there wasn't these - mothers unions and youth clubs and all that sort of thing. Then. There was nothing of that in our days. And - I
 had one cousin, he was the same age as me, the last two of the generation, and of course he was one of these that - must be everything up to date you know, I told you about - did - the television didn't is? He said to me one day, he says, you know Ethel 
-
 he said, the time will come, he says, you know, where Sunday schools won't be needed. I said, oh? No, he says, the youth clubs - will take their place. I says, thank God help the children of England if they don't get anything more than they get there. Be
cause, I says, my opinion is the Sunday school is the nursery for the church. They do still exist but not like they used to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Do you think your mother would have thought of herself as the wife of a tradesman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes, quite, definitely. Definite, mind you they - worked their way up from nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Do you think it was possible to work your way up from nothing in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes, I saw it in my own home. Oh yes. Oh yes, I think if you've got the - the man and wife are well mated I think it
's a lovely thing to work together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Do you remember anybody being described as a real lady or a real gentleman?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh there are a few about. I look on doctor Vevan as a real gentleman. And I'm sure his wife is very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When you were a child if somebody had said to you he'd a real gentleman, what would you have thought that meant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
I should think it out. Before I said anything. Oh yes, you can soon - you can soon find it out. It don't take long. I never was as Mrs - Wiggins said to me, y
ou haven't met her have you? I don't remember what it was she was talking - well she says, you see, you can talk to people. I says, Hilda, what do you mean? Well, she says, you don't rush at anybody before you know them. Oh no, I said, I like to feel my w
a
y, know where I am. No what you may and what mayn't say. But I says it makes all the difference you know. She said - I said, well I get on with most people, says, if you rub me up the wrong way and then I don't say much. It isn't wise is it. You can soon 
say the wrong thing. And they don't forget it. No, it's the pity of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Do you remember seeing policemen around when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh bless you, yes, we used to have three or four about, never see one now, I don't know where they get.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I wasn't afraid of him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your mother ever say when you were naughty I'll call the policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh no, I never heard anything of that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How do you think he treated the ordinary people in Woodstock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Who?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 The police in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Well they was all friendly. We used to have - three about here. That friend that lived with me from - had to leave her home in Essex and died here, her father was a policeman. 'Cos I heard her say to - someone one ni
ght - she says, Ethel will go to bed and I don't think she'd care whether the place was locked up or not. She says - if she'd heard as much as I have from policemen she'd be more particular. Well I says, it never worried me, I didn't think I should be kid
napped.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I know they did. But I was never denied anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What did you think about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you mind that your parents had to do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. I thought it was all life and that was it. But you see I've come out at the top. Now - through their hard work and care and - that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What difference did it make to your family when you were a girl if your father was ever ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 He was never out of work. No, of course father was a bronchial asthma subject, and for the l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9926461\charrsid5728063 ast - let's s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
ee what, he was eighty - eighty six when he passed away, but - at seventy - and - he had some bad - I had a few rough times with him and his asthma, cruel complaint you know - asthma.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When your father was ill did you ever get any help from anywhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Oh I didn't want any help, I knew how to manage him. I got so used to it you see and he depended on me for everything. He was - had a - Doctor Moore th
at was here then - well, at that time, he said to me, he says, Mrs Morgan you needn't send for me, he says, only -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Were there many panel patients?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh was a good many I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You were never on the panel though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What about - did you ever get parish help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
No, certainly not. Oh no. No, - nothing of that. It was hard work and hard going but we always kept our heads above the waters and - that - coal strike was the worst thing, that - not this last one, one before, was a time. Six months you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 If there was somebody in the district in Old Woodstock that other people very strongly disapproved of, how would they show it, do you know?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I don't - I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You don't ever remember rough music?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Never remember what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, never. No. Woodstock was too select for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 But you knew it went on in other places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes. I said the other day, I says I knew a time when I said well - Woodstock was quiet and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9926461\charrsid5728063 peacea}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 ble and everyb
ody was neighbourly, but not now, I don't see - there's that old friend of mine said, well, she says, you know my child, you must remember, it's a new generation and they weren't brought up as we were. I - that's my favourite flower. Roses and lilies of t
he valley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You said you had heard of rough music being done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Mm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You said you heard of people having rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Ah, but not in Woodstock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Whereabouts was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh I don't know, somewhere round the outskirts you - you - you want to take me further back than I can go you know, at my age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Were you ever given lessons by one of your parents or a tutor or a governess at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. Uncle at the gas works, he taught me the piano, he'd got a nice piano uncle had down there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When did you first go to school? How old were you, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Oh seven I should think, it was a little nursery school. And then of course - I went to a private school round the other street, and the schoolmistress passed out and there w
as nothing left but the National school. And the doctor told mother, he said, if you send to her to that school it'll kill here she'll never stand it. But then there was no help - and I did go and I always got on, I liked the teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 That was the national school you went to when you were seven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
National school. Yes. And - no, I was ten then. And - I thought it was funny, she said to me one day - they wanted to make a teacher of me you see. And I knew it wouldn't work because we were dissenters 
and they were church people, it was church you see and - I didn't quite like the idea, well, I says, for one thing I couldn't study and teach too, and then strange to say later on I was told I ought to have got into a gentleman's nursery like Blenheim. I 
thought heaven help me. Then I went - rag stabbing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What time of day did you go to school, what time in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What time did you come back, did you come back at dinnertime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes. And back at two. And - well it wa
s the same as the workroom routine really we went at nine, we came home at - half past twelve and - tea at half past four, then we went back to work 'til seven o'clock you see in the work room. Especially if you got a morning order, a wedding order. That 
had to be done you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Was it a mixed school, boys and girls went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
No, there was the three different departments. There was the boys school, and the girls school and then the infants. Anything else? I should have thought it had worn it threadbare.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Walked, we didn't - we weren't taken in motors and fetched home as they are today and ruined in the process. 'Cos that's what it means.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How long did it take you from here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well was up by the station, well there isn't a station now is there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 About five minutes or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Oh about that. Do you know, that station - was opened - the night before my brother was born. I suppose it didn't pay and that was it. They had to close it you see and now it's all built on isn't it? So they tell me. Oh I said, I don't want to see it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Who took you to school, did anybody take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I went myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Even when you were seven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes. Well you know there wasn't the traffic about, yo
u were safe then. You're not now are you. I was saying to the other day, my - my friend came in, she was so tired, well I says, I should think it takes you - women double the time with your shopping - waiting to cross the road. Well we had the best time, 
we took life easy then. We wasn't rushed and bustled about.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you like school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes, I always liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well always got on with them. The last twelve months I was at school I had a class on my own
, that's why gave the schoolmistress the idea that I ought to take up teaching but - I didn't, I went dressmaking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did the teachers say certain things were important in life, like manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, they didn't bother much about them. I saw an article
 in the paper only last week - we weren't taught what they're taught now and shown on the television I thought no, good job you're not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 But you were taught manners at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes, but then you see - in a home if - if parents have got good manners - their children naturally imitate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What about tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Ay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Tidiness at school, taught to be tidy were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 That was a gift with me. If anything couldn't be found, oh well Ethel's put it somewhere, yes, I said, and if you put thing
s down in the proper places you could do I used to say you wouldn't have to hunt for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Were you taught ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 They didn't mind if you had an accent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh no. We weren't so particular as that. They thought you'd acqu
ire that at - company you got in as you got older you see. But it isn't so. And that sort of thing we were taught in the home.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Were you punished at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Were I what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Punished at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, I never got into much trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 But were children punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Not - no. No. You see, we had nice teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Nobody ever got the stick or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. I never saw it there. Did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes, as much as they could but you see father never went to school after he was eight you see, and mother was out at service at ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did they ask what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. Well we only did reading and writing - arithmetic, grammar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did they ever come and visit the school or talk to the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. They do now don't they? So one of my friends were saying. Did more good in the world than any religious sect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What class of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 People that don't go to a place of worship. They can get them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Evangelicals you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 MM. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Is that more like the chapel was in your day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 They went out more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 That's what they should do. Not sit at home and wait. That's not - what they're
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you go on to another school after the National?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
No, and when I left the national school at sixteen - and I came home and - I went to the dressmaking and then - even then I had certain work to do in the home you see, well mother was never very strong. And sometimes it took you all t
he time to answer the door bell.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Would you have stayed on at school if you could?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
No, I wouldn't. I couldn't. I wasn't strong enough for that. And - one day I I discovered that father and my husband was - laying plans to have the phone in. Well I let them get on with it for a certain time, and when I thought it was nearly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 After you left school did you go to any evening classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. When I left school I was at home. We all spent our evenings at home. We was quite content. Of course all
 through the spring and summer I was out in the garden, and so was my husband. We loved the garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you have any regrets about school, about your school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, never. No. 'Cos they had - we had nice teachers. There was - a headmaster in the bo
ys and I suppose one or two of us, and there was the headmistress and two more, and - three I think in the infants school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Do you think you learnt a lot at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I learnt more away than I did there, and I've been learning ever since.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you have any jobs when you were still at school that earned you money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. No, we didn't do that in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What was your first full time job? The first job you had when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well you see I went straight into the dressmakin
g. I had - did nothing else from then 'til I was married. And then of course - my husband and I we didn't have a home on our own. We had our own rooms here but we never had another house, because you see - it was all in the business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You did the dressmaking in Woodstock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How many people worked there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Two. Besides Mrs Carsford. That was the friend that lived here and died here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You and Mrs Carsford went there as girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Mm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh no, Lal was a good bit older than I was, my friend that worked there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Were you trained as a dressmaker there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Why, you learn it just as you went along you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What sort of things did you make?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh I don't know, evening dresses, beach dresses and - wedding dresses and mourning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You made them for the gentry then usually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh well - very good class of people it was you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Takes me back years now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you like that, working there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes, we were very happy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How long did you have to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Well we went at nine in the morning, was there 'til seven at night. I remember Mrs. Carsford's husband come up in the workroom one day, she was working at - we were working at a bridge - bridge party dress and - she - held it u
p, she says, dad, what do you think of this? Oh, he says, I think it's very nice. Who's it for? Oh Mrs so and so. Oh Lor', he says, another launching new fashion. Another - yes, another launching new fashion. It's just his way, 'cos he didn't approve of h
er. Oh we had some very nice work up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Would you have preferred any other sort of job do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, not unless I could have been a florist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You couldn't be a florist in Woodstock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh no, because you see we'd no means of transp
ort or anything. In those days. If people had to go to the infirmary they had to go in a carrier's cart you know. Was no ambulance, nothing in that in those days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Do you think that going to work changed your attitude to life at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Not at all.
 Not at all. You see, I suppose I was contented. And that was it. Father and mother and home, was my all 'til I married. And then there was one more to be added to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When you started work do you think it changed your attitude to your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Not a bit. Not a bit, nothing would have changed my attitude there. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You went on going on to chapel with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes, we had our chapel and our Sunday school and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When did you start teaching in the Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I don't k
now. I - I can't quite remember. How I come to take to it first. But - at one time - we never - closed our Sunday school whatever happened but there came a time when - measles was so bad - it really wasn't hardly worthwhile. And mother had got a very nice
 
class of lads, about - fourteen or fifteen. Did I tell you? No. And she was worried about these boys, she said, I'm afraid if they - have to close for a few Sundays I'm going to lose those boys. Well, our father, says you can get over that, he said - I ca
n
 stay in the office Sunday, which he never did you see, never had the fire in there, we were all together, he said, I can stay in the office and he says - you can have the back - the big room, and Ethel got the piano to give you song and - he says, she'd 
h
ave the worst of it 'cos she'd have extra grate to clean on the Monday morning. Oh well, I says, that won't matter. And - they had a very nice time. And when the time was - done, these boys didn't want to go back to Sunday school. Well we finished up with
 a tea party and she didn't lose any of the boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Do you remember a great difference between trained craftsmen and workmen in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. You see, in the first place - my husband was apprenticed in Banbury. To - I don't - tin work and all tha
t sort - he could turn his hand to anything you see. And then the man died - and while his father was on the look out for something for him you see, father was busy and - he stayed here, he liked the horses. And I was here as well, so that was it. What el
se?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you go on spending your time in the same way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you go out in the evening after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No I didn't. Well we might in the summer time be out on playing hopscotch or - hoops and sticks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Even after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Oh no. I was at home most - well I was in the garden, I didn't want anything else to do. And you see there was a certain amount of housework and we hadn't got a servant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you meet new friends, boys or girls after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Boys didn't interest me. They laugh at me - Mrs Wiggins. Anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you have any special friends after you left school and before you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. We worked all day and then George and I go off for a walk with the dog at night, and come in tired out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What age were you when you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Thirty-two. And George was five years older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How long had you known your husband then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 He came into our home when he was nineteen, as I said, to help - father and he never went away again you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Where did he come from, did he come from Banbury?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, he was apprenticed in Banbury, but his father run the Dedington gas works. Dedington and Banbury.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you save up money before you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes, a litt
le, but you see - we hadn't got to set up a home as far as that goes, we furnished one room, the sitting room downstairs - was our room but you see all the rest - I wouldn't have my bedroom altered at all. So - we did - we didn't have to have a big start 
you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How long were you engaged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Let me see. Oh about two years, I've had the ring about seventy years see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Could you describe your wedding to me?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I was mar - we were married at nine o'clock on a Boxing Day, and there was only fath
er - and the girl that was my bridesmaid and my husband, there was just the four us, early that Boxing morning. I couldn't have stood a fuss. Then we - went into chapel, it was raining hard. And when we came out the sun was shining lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you have presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes, I - had a nice lot of presents. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What did you get, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Well - the - chapel people gave us - a lovely tea service. And friends of the chapel gave us a coffee set. Oh I don't know. Different friends you know
. And one of the chapel friends gave me a lovely biscuit barrel. Oh I made a list, I don't know where I put it, but I got it all. Of course people didn't go in for wedding presents then as they do now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you have a wedding breakfast or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
No, we came home from chapel and - that minister up there, he was with us and - we had a nice day. And mother you see - mother stayed at home and - and my husband's father, and when we got home mother had got the table set for breakfast and in the centr
e of the table - there was a lovely vase of flowers, sent - or brought, I don't know which it was, the head gardener from Glimpton Park. Lovely greenhouse flowers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you go away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, we didn't go away, it was winter time. I shall have told you
 all my secrets soon shan't I. Oh it was a happy time and - on Boxing Day we should have been - this next we should have been married sixty years. And if - mother had have lived 'til August, she and father would have been their diamond wedding, and I thin
k father had rather looked forward to that. And mother you know, you could never get her to have a photo.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When you were married you went on living here with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes, we had our own rooms you see, one room downstairs. Well - of course it
 wasn't worthwhile setting up another house we were - well mother said definitely she wasn't going to stay here without me. Oh well, I says, suppose that'll settle it. Oh George was quite willing - to stay here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What was your husband's job when you were married?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Well he was here with father you see, he was apprenticed in Banbury to the - well, you call it tinkering, he could turn his hand to anything in that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 But he became a sweep when he came here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Mm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 He was a sweep when he was here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Yes, took it up you see with father, but he could do as much as his tinkering work you know. He made a lovely kettle for me downstairs, I suppose it's worn out now With strict orders I was not to let anybody working here put any hard water
 in it, he says you keep that for your own har - for your own soft water, don't you have any hard water put in it. I always had it. Because there's a lovely soft water well in the garden you see. I like soft water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Do you think your husband liked his work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Oh yes, he was always at work, quite happy. As a - he never settled down - he was very fond of singing. But - oh we had some nice times. Of course that big - that big - coal strike you see was what fixed George, he had a bad breakdown for three
 years. It was a terrible time that was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Which strike was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Mm? Not the last one, one before, a very -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I want to ask you about housekeeping when you were first married, that would be up to just the and of the great war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 The housek
eeping money was men - handed over to me, mother says, I'm not going to handle it my child, you take it. Well, I says, all right, I don't mind. And - I heard mother say to father one day - yes, she says, I think Ethel handles the housekeeping money - well
 
don't you? Yes, he says, as long as she don't cut it too fine on us. Well I says in the first place you're going to stop going to the butchers for me. Because I says you get talking to Mr Steel, and it's a few ounces over here and a few ounces over there,
 
I says, it doesn't make a better dinner but I got to pay for it, so I says, I'll see to that for the future. Oh all right, he said, he didn't go to the butchers anymore. I had to put my foot down sometimes you know. Although I like easy - I liked a pleasa
nt life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 So you did the housekeeping for your mother and father as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes, we all lived together you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you ever know how much your husband earned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes, there was no secrets in any way. Pity there is today - come to that. Oh yes, I had to do the housekeeping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did he give you your housekeeping money out of what he earned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Oh I came - had it off of father for the lot you see. But of course - after the father went it was in our hands altogether and then - George 
was very good, he used to say sometimes when he put my money out, have you got enough, do you want some more because you've only got to say. I said, no, I've got quite as much as I want. I thought if I don't have it I shan't spend it shall I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You went on living on here and you went on having a washerwoman coming in, that was all, you didn't have anybody else to help in the house?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, she came washing and one day for extra cleaning. Oh I shouldn't I like to get a scrubbing brush and a bucket of water now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You said you had lots of people living here at times when you were first married and that, who was living here, were they relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes. Well - grandma was here six years. And then my husband's father when he gave up the - Dedington ga
s works, he was here six months. Then my - I don't know as it interests you does it, but my - mother's - brother, only brother, you see, he had a bad accident, he had a compound fracture, and when he came out of the Radcliffe, we had him and he had to hav
e a room you see. I had to look after - I looked after him. And oh dear, it was one after another all the time. When my friend passed away - the last one, they didn't think I should live here alone. And I - it had been such a strain with one and another.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you ever take in lodgers, who paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you make the clothes after you were married for your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes, I done mother's and mine - made all their shirts. Oh yes, I wouldn't let anybody else. Oh I did all the shirt maki
ng. Poor father, he said to me, soon after mother passed away, he says, oh dear, Ethel, my shirts are getting bad. So I said, don't worry, I says, I'll soon make some - no, he says, you won't, he says, you've got more to do now than you can do. I says, we
ll - are you prepared to wear a ready made shirt? No, he says. Well then, I says, that settles it doesn't it. He never did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Your husband would buy his own suits would he?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes, I didn't interfere with that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your husband mend shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Oh no. He was a rare one for tend - looking after shoes but oh no. No, I did all the needlework. I've never regretted it. You know - I said to a friend of mine the other day, her daughter wasn't fond of needlework, I said, no, I said my opinion is 
that a well stocked work basket is one of the most needful things in a home. 'Cos you see in those days it was a case of make and mend, you had to do it. I says, we couldn't go into - Woolworths or anywhere like that and get a readymade shirt, dress, and 
when it was done it was done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What sort of jobs did your husband do about the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
My husband? Oh father and George, well neither of them were domesticated, they could handle the teapot but - if they trouble about anything else. But anything in the way of repairing it was always done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 And painting and stuff as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh no, nothing of that, I didn't see any of 'em - either of 'em - ever handled a paintbrush, that wasn't in their line.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What about things like cutting up wood and making up the fires and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh I had it to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You had to do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480212\charrsid5728063 M}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
m. Mm. Oh it never went hard with me, I had four grates staring me in the - face every morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You had to black}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480212\charrsid5728063 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 lead those did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes, and you can't get black}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480212\charrsid5728063 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 lead now can you? No, well I think it's a great shame. Oh they were happy - there were five different ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Could you tell me a bit about meals when you were married, after you were married. Where did you eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 In the kitchen. Bec
ause you see - well our dinner and tea - they were black you see. We always had supper in the other room, and we had all our meals there on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You were talking about your range just now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You cooked on the range did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh
 yes. Oh yes, I got a gas stove in the further place, I hadn't had it new long when I crocked in. But still it's there, I said, well - the time might come, I don't know, when I might have to have someone living in but I - not - nothing's too much trouble.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What time did you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Well you see, father and George very often out here between four and five, but father always bought - he brought mother's and my breakfast up while my husband went and got the van and that ready for the work you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I want to talk about meals now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Before 1918, but after you were married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Mm. Well what about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When did you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well of course as I said yesterday, father and my husband you see, they were out early 
in the morning. They used to - well father got a cup of tea and - and the food, while my husband went and got the van ready you see, so we had ours upstairs. Well then, we used to - have dinner at half past twelve. And that was one thing I kicked about, I
 said, if they couldn't come in to meals the proper time they'd be cleared away. They knew I meant it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What sort of things did you have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh only bread and butter or marmalade. I don't think father reckoned to have anything to eat. Y
ou see - we always had supper at eight and that was as mother used to say they expected as much then as a dinner time. So that you see father didn't want much in the morning but his - cup of tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What sort of things did you have to eat for lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Well - well did - yes, that's right, I like that best. Well it was always - meat, and potato and always a pudding of some sort. And if I was a - lone I had a cup of tea after. Well then you see teatime it was - bread and butter and - honey or jam or - ca
ke, all home made you see, homemade cake and home make - I used to make cake about three times a week, a cake and a - that was it you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 And then you had supper at about eight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 At eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Your husband and your father came home for tea as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes, five o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 And then they went out again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
No. George would be busy when down - he went down in his shop and was tinkering. He did a lot of that work you know. And - oh - then father'd settle down with his paper and his}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480212\charrsid5728063  }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480212\charrsid5728063 ip}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 e. He never had any cigarette smoking indoors. I wouldn't put up with that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 But he smoked his pipe indoors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Always a pipe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Then you had supper at eight all together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You said you had a lot for supper, was it a big meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Well father and George did, as I say, it was like a dinner to them. I generally had bread and cheese and cocoa, I always used to make mother - well three times a week I used to make her Bengers food and three times a - egg custard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What would George and your father have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
George had coffee as a rule, but father had a glass of beer, when he was recommended it, until then he didn't, much to my brother's disgust. Of course we were all teetotallers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What did they have to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Suppertime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well as I said, cold meat and - vegetable you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you make bread after you were married here?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Make it? No, I should like a slice now. I said to Mrs Wiggins - you see her husband's - people was in this bake}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480212\charrsid5728063 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 hou
se, I said to her the other day, oh Hilda, I said, just one slice off those small tin loaves I used to like. Yes, she said, and you're not the only - I can't get on with this bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 But you made your own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh mother made all the jams and pickles and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you go on making it after you were married, or did your mother do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
No, I shared it. Mother would never do faddy cooking. She would never make little cakes or jam tarts and - I had to do that, but - she couldn't fancy you see, but she was a good plain cook.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What about bottling fruit after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes, I did a lot of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Out of the garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, generally - well you see they was about at work and - one would offer 'em fruit and then another. When I h
ad those two girls here, the evacuees, that was one thing that took their fancy more than any, they'd never heard of such -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What sort of fruit did you bottle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Plums as a rule. And then you see there was the pickled onions and cabbage and - mothe
r didn't do many walnuts, they didn't like them much. Well they were happy times. But of course as I said the other day - you see what that costs now for all that sort of thing. I'm not mercenary but you've got to think these things out. And - see we got 
a
 nice stove in the kitchen, well it's very old but - if mother got jam to make she - sort it over and get it ready and - put it in a preserving pan on the side of the stove you see, and let it get thoroughly warm, then as soon as dinner was over and the w
ashing up done well then - all the attention was given, that was pulled over the fire you see and - and cooked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 So you got some fruit from the farms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh where they were at work, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 But the vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh we grew our own. George grew our own.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you ever buy tinned or dried vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, not in those days, don't now. Well I don't eat vegetables you see, I don't have vegetable or meat. Myself. Mine is - princip}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480212\charrsid5728063 al}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 ly milk you see. Well - today Mrs Wiggins, she brought m
e up a lovely little bread and butter pudding. Oh I am well looked after, I look back and I think well you have been blessed. In every way. As I say on the top of all that I've got my nice memories. I'm quite contented, until comes the spring and summer t
hey come in - your garden does look nice, oh I said, be quiet, I am rested and contented but - leave the garden alone. It's been a great pleasure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you keep any pigs or chickens or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes, we had chickens. At one time. But as 
I say there was a - two horses and a pony in the stable, and there was always the dog, and three cats, father was very fond of cats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What did you do with the chickens, did you have the eggs yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh we didn't have many, in - in fact I can ha
rdly remember that now. But when grandma and grandpa were at the gas works grandma always kept chicken and ducks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 And you had the eggs from them did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Mm. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you kill the birds and have them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh I don't know what grandma did 
with them in the end, no. Of course there was a brook down there, that was always all right for the ducks. I suppose they've filled all that in now and building - down along there. Along the bottom you know. From Old Woodstock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Can you remember Christmas now when you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes, I was married Boxing Day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What sort of Christmas did you spend when you were first married, what did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh we were at home here. Father and mother and George and I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you go to chapel Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, we didn't have a service there Christmas Day. And in those days you see they used to have the watch}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15480212\charrsid5728063 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 night service New Year's Eve. No, we were married at about \{ILLEGIBLE\} clock on a Boxing morning and - that's nearly sixty years so don't 
take me back any further.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 So you stayed at home on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you have a big dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 We had the ordinary Christmas dinner you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you have presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes. I was saying the other day, I says, fancy now 
the poor little kiddies, they can't hang their stockings up now they can they with the - with the - well, all the gas and electricity, they can't tell them they're coming down the chimney now can they No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What did you do Christmas afternoon, did you sing or anything together, you and your husband and mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well after Christmas dinner we didn't want much to do, we generally read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What about Christmas Evening, Christmas night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well - I think Christmas Eve, and Christmas nigh
t - I - I was very much frightened, because you see at that time when they turned of the public houses - they was pretty merry. Well of course that's another step forward we're more - advanced and civilized now, you don't hear that now, I suppose - it's t
elevision keeps people at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Were you worried that there'd be fighting outside the house or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Mm. Quarrelling, of course we had a lot of public houses there then. More than there are now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you ever go out giving tracts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Give what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Giving tracts, temperance tracts out on Christmas at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. At one time that - years ago, after our morning service, so many of us had tracts we took round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When would that have been?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Mm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How long ago was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh a good many years, before I was married. You're muddling me up you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I'm sorry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You don't look it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Were they temperance tracts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes. Yes. Of course in those days - temperance was the biggest thing with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480212\charrsid5728063 M
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 ethodists. B
ut I don't think that's recognised now. It isn't really. I don't say people get worse for it, well we never had it in our home. I had rather a bad turn one day and one of the nurses come in and - after she said I wish to goodness I'd have known where to p
ut my hand on some brandy. I said, well - no. We were nothing for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you have any musical instruments in your home after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I'd got my piano, that's mine. No. Just the piano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You played that did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your husband play it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
No, George was fond of singing but - and so was my brother, but - they didn't - I think Henry did start learning the piano but it didn't appeal to him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What sort of things did George sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh we generally got the 
old songs you know and - Sankey's hymns on Sunday and that. I loved - I did have a nice time in the community singing Sunday night - from half past eight 'til nine, he came from Wales you see, they're lovely singers aren't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you all make music together on a Sunday night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did we what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you get together and play the piano and sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes. Yes. And - generally three - Sundays in the quarter, we had the minister or preacher with us you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 On a Sunday night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well h
e was here all day Sunday. 'Cos I used to tell mother, well, I says, we work hard all the week but - when it comes to Sunday I think we work harder still. 'Cos we never gave up our Sunday school work even if we'd got a preacher here you see. Oh yes, nice 
times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did anybody else come in to sing with you in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Just the four of you and the preacher if he was here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 We were very select. I mean if anybody came in they were welcome. Mother was never one to make a lot of friends
. Of course - we was - much in - we were as much friendly with the Banbury's as any, did you know the Banbury's? Yes. Well I've known five generations - at least. I don't - know - I don't - I don't know any of the last four sons, but of course my brother 
was up there six years. In the shop, mm. Yes, and then you see Mr Banbury and father - they were interested in the chapel work and also in the fire brigade. Of course Henry was all for ambulance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you ever sing anything apart from sacred songs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, I - there's a - bundle of my old songs downstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What sort of songs were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Oh all sorts, the old ones, oh I can't remember. The songs are not so nice today. I heard Moira Anderson sing one - one hymn - what was she in? Have you ever 
heard her? She sang a hymn that she used to sing it as - he was talking on the wireless one night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you learn any songs from your mother or father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What sort of books or newspapers did you have in the house when you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Well, we - you know, there wasn't many - papers in those days. There was a funny thing, I was talking to my friend - Mrs Townsend and - I said, you know Mrs Townsend I was thinking how different our Sundays are now to what they used to be. I says, y
ou know - in those days there wasn't a morning newspaper, there wasn't the shops kept open all day. I says, there wasn't the ice cream barrows about. No, she says, you're right. I says, there was nothing of that in our young days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What about a daily paper?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What did we - oh we didn't have a daily papers in those days all the way back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What about when you were first married, did you have a daily paper then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. We used to - there used to be the Oxford Times. And Lloyds, and I think we h
ad a - the Methodist. I think that was all. But you see, I wasn't allowed to read newspapers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Why not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Doctor's orders. Too nervy you see. Still I do now. I mean - that's one thing, since I've been fixed like this for nearly three years - I'm a 
lot better physically and - I don't suffer so much with nerves you see. 'Cos I - something happened not long age and - Mrs Wiggins, you know, you saw here I says, well you didn't tell me. No, she says I didn't tell you last night because she says I though
t you'd be awake all night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You read a lot of books, where did you get them from when you were first married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Always bought them. See I've got - these here. Oh they're all my books, I love them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Were you in a library?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Mm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Were you a member of the library?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I used to go to the library twice a week but then you see I had to give it up. So there you are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 But you were in the library when you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes. Yes. But George didn't read much, never got - beyond the 
newspaper, he picked up one or two with serials in and he got so mad because he says - they just leave off when you're getting excited. Well, I said, that's what they do it for, to sell it. Oh he said, I never thought of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What did you do on Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What did we do, which Bank Holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Whitsun, Whit Monday or August Bank Holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh we was always - we generally had somebody come in and another and \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 the garden, we never - wanted much beyond that. You see, people worked hard in those days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you go out for the day at all on Bank Holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. I couldn't go out, I could never travel you see. And I didn't want to come to that. My home was my all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 So you never went away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I went once 
or twice and they had to bring me home. I says I'm not going again, because, I said - I never enjoy it and I'm a wet blanket to other people so, I says, you needn't ask me to go out again. I didn't go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When did you first go on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh I forg
et. I went to Chelmsford once. And to Southend. And to - it didn't appeal to me and I can't bear the sea. There's two things I very much dislike, and that's the sea and toy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480212\charrsid5728063 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 land. I don't like toy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480212\charrsid5728063 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 land. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 After you were married did the way you spent Saturday change or Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh - I - didn't catch what you said. No. There was too much housework to be done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What about Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well I tell you, there was chapel and Sunday school you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 And you had classes in Sunday school didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
I had a class of girls and my mother had her boys. And it was a great bit of fun to me because - mother used to say she wouldn't have a class of girls. I used to say, no, and nothing on earth would per - get me to have a class of boys, I said, I 
shouldn't have any patience with them. And then the latter years one of the teachers said to mother, Mrs Morgan, I wish you'd take my glass of girls over, they're getting the better of me. She did, and she had her - her class of girls 'til the Sunday she 
died - Sunday before she died. Is that all going down? And I think - the latter part of father's life when he was indoors more, we were closer together then - than ever we were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you think it wrong to work on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, not if there's work to do, but I shouldn't do what didn't want to be done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What about children playing on a Sunday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Well, mother had always got scripture books, and scripture puzzles, you know. You fitted the bits in. Used to love those, I wonder if they have any 
of them now. Scripture pictures you see. No, I shouldn't think so, too old fashioned. Still children are not taught like that today, they're not like children. At least I don't think so. I'd like you to see that little grandchild of Mrs Wiggins.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You went on going to the chapel after you were married, were you going to the Baptist by then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
No, no, the Methodist. We were married at the Methodist and I believe George and I were the last - the last married there after it was closed, and father's was the last service, burial.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When did the Methodist down there close then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh I don't know. How many years ago it is. I couldn't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Was it before the last war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes. That was a lively time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You didn't belong to any clubs or anything organised by the chapel then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
No. Not then. I suppose they've got a social club here - somewhere round the other street but - I don't know nothing about it now. I've lost count.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Was grace said at meals after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Who said that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Well it all depended you see who was here, and down at the gas house they always had morning prayer. All that's forgotten now isn't it. We used to have a lovely Band of Hope connected with our chapel. Used to have some lovely - evenings there you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you help run the Bank of Hope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, I wasn't old enough to do anything but I was always there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You were a member when you were girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did that go on when you were older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, that bro
ke up you see like everything else, the children went and - the pity of it is to my idea, parents don't take the interest. That's where you lose hold you see. Like they used to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You didn't have family prayers here then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. We was never together much you see in the morning. Did you in your home? No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you have them on Sunday at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
No. No, we had the service all day, mother - George and father and - and then mother and I was in the Sunday school and when we came out we generally
 had a walk up the park. Mother used to say, you know, Ethel, you seem to know everybody. Well I says, you see being in the Sunday school, then I says look at the people who come to the door on business. You're always on the go. Don't know as it did us an
y harm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Could I ask you, after you were married, did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
No. Politics never worried me, and they don't now. I suppose it ought, but it doesn't. I'm not satisfied with our government now. Are you? No. Don't know what to make of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your husband take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. I used to say it wasn't worthwhile sho}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480212\charrsid5728063 w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 ing our blood pressure up for politics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What did your father think about that, about you not being interested in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh it 
didn't worry him. No. No. He used to say, I've heard it so many times, well it doesn't matter whose in Parliament or what the politics are, we've all got to work just the same. That's what one of my friends says.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your husband vote in the elections before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Do you know what he voted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Mm. Mm. I think he did, but - I can't go as far back, you see we were never interested in politics. There was the chapel and the Sunday school, well then there was father interested in the fire
 you see and my husband and my brother in the ambulance and what with one thing and another there wasn't time for much else.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You couldn't remember how your husband voted at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. No. No, you know the last - time there was a - an election for
 the council you know - and - there was on particular man - I admired very much and my husband says well you must go and vote for him. I said, no, I don't think so. He says, yes he says, come on, I'll take you. And he saw the man after he did get in. He s
ays, you know if it hadn't have been for you my wife wouldn't have come out. He was a nice man, he's passed out now. But he got in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When you and your husband wasn't working -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Weren't working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What did you do when you weren't working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh there was always something to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you ever go out together in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Of course we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Where did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Along out the back gates and along the Green Lanes and take the dog. Lovely it was. That - the other old lady that's 
older than me that lives at Stonesfield, she lived at the top of the lane. Oh, she says, the times I've seen you and Mr George come out of that back gates with the dog.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 So you'd do that quite often in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 In the summer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What about in the winter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Well - I used to be sewing, mother generally knitted, and if they'd - if they wasn't looking at the papers they dropped off to sleep, we had good company you know. Yes. Oh we were very happy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What time did your husband get home from work in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh George'd finish at six - at five o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Then he'd go out into his workshop after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh he'd go down the workshop or do the garden and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What sort of things did he make in his workshop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well it was mostly repairing you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 He did that like a job did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes, that was hobby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 He'd mend pots and pans for people in Woodstock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes. A - a man came in one day, and he was talking, Mrs Morgan, he says, I expect you've missed Mr Geor
ge terribly as far as it goes. Oh yes, I says, if a kettle or anything run out, I says, he'd snatch it up and take it off and bring it in next time he came. Of course he'd always got his dog with him. Didn't dare touch anything belonging to him. Not if Ni
ck was about. If he left his shoes on the fender and I wanted to go to the oven I daren't touch 'em if he wasn't there. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How many evenings would he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Was what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How many evenings a week would your husband spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Stay at home? Every evening. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When did he go to the fire service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well that all depended when they had a drill night you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did they have a drill night once a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Once or twice in the - but it was different then you see, i
t was voluntary firemen then. Yes. And they used to go to - camp once a year for three or four days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Whereabouts did they go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well that all depended, when that - war broke out the - the big war, they was at Hastings. And then when war was declar
ed they didn't think they'd get home that night. But they did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Which war was that, the last war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, war before. Did you ever hear of Winifred Graham the writer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you or your husband belong to any savings clubs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What about sports, did he take part in sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 George was no sportsman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Nothing at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did he go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. You - Mrs Wiggins you see was - oh her son lives by the water. Always fishing. Well when he isn't at work, he
's the - he works in Blenheim Gardens you see. Her Ken does.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you have bicycles, did your husband have a bicycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh he rode a bicycle, he tried to teach me but it didn't come off. I nearly came off. So I left it alone. I was fond of walking.
 I used to love - after tea in the summer if George was busy to go through Bladen, through the park. Lovely that was. I used to go alone. I al - I always liked that walk through the park, through Bladen. And that again I shouldn't know Bladen now. Well of
 course it belongs to Blenheim and that's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did your husband go out on his bicycle at all in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes, he used to ride a bicycle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Where would he go on that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well it all depended. His real home was Dedington you see, used to go there sometime on a Sunday, but not very often. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you ever go to a theatre or to concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
I've never been to a theatre, I've never been to a dance and I've never handled cards. But I've been perfectly happy. Home and the chapel and the - the walks was my boundary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you ever go to sacred concerts or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes, we used to have a concert up in the Town Hall sometimes. Very nice. They were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What about the cinema?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, I - oh we had a cinema over the
re - oh I don't know - where - you know, just over the road it was the fire station and then they took - took it off but - he - he was a bachelor, I - and his name was Morgan. And I used to go occasionally and sometimes father would. And I used to say som
etimes, I think I'll come over tonight. No, he says, don't do that, he says, my picture tonight won't suit you. I'll tell you when it's nice to come. It was very good of him, he spent a Christmas with us once. He was there and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you go on keeping pets after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You still had your pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Yes. It was a very funny thing, I'd got the cats - and Nicky the dog went first, we had to have him put to sleep. And then one of the cats was run over. And the other two I had to have put to sleep. I never had any more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You went on doing your gardening did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What did you grow in your garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Mm? What did we grow? Roses and - oh all sorts of flowers and then there was the lawn you see and the vegetable garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you look after the flowers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I did, yes. George was no flower gardener.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 He was a vegetable gardener?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Mm. Father really wasn't very interested in gardening. But we both liked it. Many a night - I've - I've come to bed an
d left my husband talking over the wall to Mrs Wiggins's father-in-law. It gets to nine o'clock - eleven o'clock, I saw the street light go out and I thought, oh dear. I'd go downstairs, fast asleep on the sofa and the light on and the wireless on. So I t
hought then, that's the time a man's a nuisance. Still they enjoyed the chat over the wall, and I thought well, better be there than the public house. It's always a blessing behind it see. If you can find it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What about your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well - we had any - much time for anything - interests - really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Just the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well as I say there was the fire service and the ambulance and - they had certain meetings you see. One night - oh
 it was after ten o'clock - the doctor that was here then - well he was here when my brother died and I think he was terribly upset about it but - one night, after ten o'clock, he came over for my brother, he had a young man broke - brought into the Kings
 Arms over the road you know, and he had an accident, put his shoulder out, and he come over for my brother to come and help him put it in. Well he was single handed you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did anybody outside the family help you in the house at all, a friend or a neighbour or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, it was the other way about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You did that did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Other people needed help. Yes. Still there was always plenty willing you know. We didn't have a very much put -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When you were first married would you go and help older people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Not a lot, there was an old couple in there, I always looked after them, got their libraries and that in the winter, well I was with the old lady when she - passed out. In fact I spent the latter part of my - working time in her work
room, she was very nice, and I was there - several of us, I used to go. There was another old - two old ladies, I used to go out the back way after tea on Sunday and take 'em a few flowers and a few books and - they looked for that you know. - It wasn't m
uch but it gave them pleasure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 How often did you go on seeing your other relatives after you were married or to George's relatives, did you go to Dedington much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I didn't, no. George used to go occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What about your grandmother and grandfather? Did you go and see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh I was always down the gas works.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Even after you were married?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Our happiest time of my life was down there. Yes. They came from Essex. Mother was born in Essex.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 When your grandmother and grandfather got old they came and lived with you didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Grandpa didn't, he died down there, grandma lived with us for six years. She was in bed three years, I said how history repeated itself. She was in bed three years and so I have been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What about - those were your mother's parents, what about your father's parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 I don't re - oh grandpa Morgan died with us, not in this house, one up further over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Then your husbands father or mother came to live with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, neither. No. No.
 George's - father - he - he - his eldest daughter kept house for him. But she died here. George's sister died here. Well I tell you we've had seven deaths in this house, and then folks thought I should stay, I says, I shall. 'Cos every home holds a memor
y. And I don't let it get me down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you and George have friends in Woodstock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You and George have friends in Woodstock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 We were all friendly and their - see their work took them about and they had plenty of friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Where did you see your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Were did we see them? OH we only met casually, we didn't do visiting. No. We didn't have those - elevens in the morning now then you know as they do now and meeting together. Wasn't time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Oh yes. Oh yes. I - it's - was talking one day about people being so jealous. I said, well - I'm inclined to pity jealous people for they must have a miserable time. I think. But I says I don't think I was ever jealous of anyone. The only thing
 I said would have roused me would if another woman tried to steal my husband, and I said, don't know what might happen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 You said George used to talk to the man next door over the wall?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did he ever go and visit his friends, other tradesmen in Woodstock in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No, because you see their work brought them up against so many friends that they were all people - all friendly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you have friends who'd come and visit you at all during the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. Well you got pl
enty of company up in the workroom, didn't want any more at night. 'Cos we worked 'til seven o'clock. And by the time you got him you didn't want much else to do, sides, I'd always got plenty of sewing and that waiting for me at home 'cos mother didn't li
ke needlework, and she wouldn't have it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 After you were married did you and George invite friends into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. Anybody come was welcome but - we generally got someone here. And as I say, three times in the quarter we had the minister or pre
achers, we always liked those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 If somebody did come to see you would you offer them something to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Oh yes, they was welcome.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What sort of thing would you give them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Well all depended what you'd got about wouldn't it. 
That's what I say, I don't keep anything in the house now because you see - Mrs Wiggins sees to all that and has it at home you see. But things have altered now haven't they? But sometimes I look back and I think it's amazing how things have altered.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did people come to see you without an invitation, just casually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Yes. I'll tell you what happened once, are you going to put that bit - take that down? It was one bank holiday, and mother was just getting over the shingles and I - we'd had six months
 - three months bad time with her, she was still more or less of an invalid, and do you know, that day three different people come, friends and relatives to and I had to get tea for them. I says, to mother I says, well this has finished it, I'm not going 
to have any more of this. I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you go out and visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
Mm? No, not very often, I'd got a few special friends but - as I tell you we were very conservative in that way, we - all worked hard and we didn't need a lot. I should like to get at some of the housework now though. Still - times gone by now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
People often say that they used to make their own amusements in those days, did you and George make your own amusements after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did we have our own amu
sements? Yes, we were - was happy enough. They used to play draughts some nights, and - but you see, we were in our room as a rule in the evening, the front room you see. And father and mother were in the middle room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 What did you do, you played draughts, did you play any other games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
We used to play draughts but - mother and I generally kept at work 'til supper time. And she'd settle down with a book, and that - mother had the advantage of me there, you know, it didn't matter who was in the room
 and who was talking, it didn't interfere with here, but I couldn't read. She'd get quite lost. Who supplies you with the foolscap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did you ever have to struggle to make ends}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480212\charrsid5728063  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 meet when you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 No. Got past that stage then, but of cours
e - I think father and mother had a hard struggle in their younger days. Although I wasn't allowed to know much about it but I wasn't blind. I was never denied anything. I remember once - was when I was getting over the breakdown after my brother died and
 
- I remember the doctor said to father, he says, you know what she needs is a port wine every day. But he says knowing your principles I'm afraid to suggest it. Father says, you can suggest what you like, he says, she shall have it whatever it costs. And 
I did have it. And - I used to have a glass of - in the morning, and once or twice I was extra tired and - say in the evening, I think I shall have another little glass of port. Father said, no you don't have Ethel, one glass a day is quite enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10510162 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 Did it make any difference to the family budget if your husband was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2708801 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063 
No, he didn't - he didn't have much illness. Of course he was - the last three years he - well of course it was thrombosis you see. Won - wonderfully strong, well they all were, father was. Of course h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15480212\charrsid5728063 e used to have these asthmatic}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1245763\charrsid5728063  bouts but - I got into the way of knowing how to manage him, that was it.
\par }}